277 /*
278  * Array with names and number of arguments of all internal functions
279  * MUST BE KEPT SORTED IN strcmp() ORDER FOR BINARY SEARCH!
280  */
281 typedef struct
282 {
283  char *f_name; // function name
284  char f_min_argc; // minimal number of arguments
285  char f_max_argc; // maximal number of arguments
286  char f_argtype; // for method: FEARG_ values
287  void (*f_func)(typval_T *args, typval_T *rvar);
288  // implementation of function
289 } funcentry_T;
290 
291 // values for f_argtype; zero means it cannot be used as a method
292 #define FEARG_1 1 // base is the first argument
293 #define FEARG_2 2 // base is the second argument
294 #define FEARG_3 3 // base is the third argument
295 #define FEARG_4 4 // base is the fourth argument
296 #define FEARG_LAST 9 // base is the last argument
297

870 /*
871  * Function given to ExpandGeneric() to obtain the list of internal
872  * or user defined function names.
873  */
874  char_u *
875 get_function_name(expand_T *xp, int idx)
876 {
877  static int intidx = -1;
878  char_u *name;
879 
880  if (idx == 0)
881  intidx = -1;
882  if (intidx < 0)
883  {
884  name = get_user_func_name(xp, idx);
885  if (name != NULL)
886  return name;
887  }
888  if (++intidx < (int)(sizeof(global_functions) / sizeof(funcentry_T)))
889  {
890  STRCPY(IObuff, global_functions[intidx].f_name);
891  STRCAT(IObuff, "(");
892  if (global_functions[intidx].f_max_argc == 0)
893  STRCAT(IObuff, ")");
894  return IObuff;
895  }
896 
897  return NULL;
898 }
899 
900 /*
901  * Function given to ExpandGeneric() to obtain the list of internal or
902  * user defined variable or function names.
903  */
904  char_u *
905 get_expr_name(expand_T *xp, int idx)
906 {
907  static int intidx = -1;
908  char_u *name;
909 
910  if (idx == 0)
911  intidx = -1;
912  if (intidx < 0)
913  {
914  name = get_function_name(xp, idx);
915  if (name != NULL)
916  return name;
917  }
918  return get_user_var_name(xp, ++intidx);
919 }
920 
921 /*
922  * Find internal function "name" in table "global_functions".
923  * Return index, or -1 if not found
924  */
925  static int
926 find_internal_func(char_u *name)
927 {
928  int first = 0;
929  int last;
930  int cmp;
931  int x;
932 
933  last = (int)(sizeof(global_functions) / sizeof(funcentry_T)) - 1;
934 
935  // Find the function name in the table. Binary search.
936  while (first <= last)
937  {
938  x = first + ((unsigned)(last - first) >> 1);
939  cmp = STRCMP(name, global_functions[x].f_name);
940  if (cmp < 0)
941  last = x - 1;
942  else if (cmp > 0)
943  first = x + 1;
944  else
945  return x;
946  }
947  return -1;
948 }
949 
950  int
951 has_internal_func(char_u *name)
952 {
953  return find_internal_func(name) >= 0;
954 }
955 
956  int
957 call_internal_func(
958  char_u *name,
959  int argcount,
960  typval_T *argvars,
961  typval_T *rettv)
962 {
963  int i;
964 
965  i = find_internal_func(name);
966  if (i < 0)
967  return ERROR_UNKNOWN;
968  if (argcount < global_functions[i].f_min_argc)
969  return ERROR_TOOFEW;
970  if (argcount > global_functions[i].f_max_argc)
971  return ERROR_TOOMANY;
972  argvars[argcount].v_type = VAR_UNKNOWN;
973  global_functions[i].f_func(argvars, rettv);
974  return ERROR_NONE;
975 }
976 
977 /*
978  * Invoke a method for base->method().
979  */
980  int
981 call_internal_method(
982  char_u *name,
983  int argcount,
984  typval_T *argvars,
985  typval_T *rettv,
986  typval_T *basetv)
987 {
988  int i;
989  int fi;
990  typval_T argv[MAX_FUNC_ARGS + 1];
991 
992  fi = find_internal_func(name);
993  if (fi < 0)
994  return ERROR_UNKNOWN;
995  if (global_functions[fi].f_argtype == 0)
996  return ERROR_NOTMETHOD;
997  if (argcount + 1 < global_functions[fi].f_min_argc)
998  return ERROR_TOOFEW;
999  if (argcount + 1 > global_functions[fi].f_max_argc)
1000  return ERROR_TOOMANY;
1001 
1002  if (global_functions[fi].f_argtype == FEARG_LAST)
1003  {
1004  // base value goes last
1005  for (i = 0; i < argcount; ++i)
1006  argv[i] = argvars[i];
1007  argv[argcount] = *basetv;
1008  }
1009  else if (global_functions[fi].f_argtype == FEARG_2)
1010  {
1011  // base value goes second
1012  argv[0] = argvars[0];
1013  argv[1] = *basetv;
1014  for (i = 1; i < argcount; ++i)
1015  argv[i + 1] = argvars[i];
1016  }
1017  else if (global_functions[fi].f_argtype == FEARG_3)
1018  {
1019  // base value goes third
1020  argv[0] = argvars[0];
1021  argv[1] = argvars[1];
1022  argv[2] = *basetv;
1023  for (i = 2; i < argcount; ++i)
1024  argv[i + 1] = argvars[i];
1025  }
1026  else if (global_functions[fi].f_argtype == FEARG_4)
1027  {
1028  // base value goes fourth
1029  argv[0] = argvars[0];
1030  argv[1] = argvars[1];
1031  argv[2] = argvars[2];
1032  argv[3] = *basetv;
1033  for (i = 3; i < argcount; ++i)
1034  argv[i + 1] = argvars[i];
1035  }
1036  else
1037  {
1038  // FEARG_1: base value goes first
1039  argv[0] = *basetv;
1040  for (i = 0; i < argcount; ++i)
1041  argv[i + 1] = argvars[i];
1042  }
1043  argv[argcount + 1].v_type = VAR_UNKNOWN;
1044 
1045  global_functions[fi].f_func(argv, rettv);
1046  return ERROR_NONE;
1047 }
1048 
1049 /*
1050  * Return TRUE for a non-zero Number and a non-empty String.
1051  */
1052  int
1053 non_zero_arg(typval_T *argvars)
1054 {
1055  return ((argvars[0].v_type == VAR_NUMBER
1056  && argvars[0].vval.v_number != 0)
1057  || (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_SPECIAL
1058  && argvars[0].vval.v_number == VVAL_TRUE)
1059  || (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_STRING
1060  && argvars[0].vval.v_string != NULL
1061  && *argvars[0].vval.v_string != NUL));
1062 }
1063 
1064 /*
1065  * Get the lnum from the first argument.
1066  * Also accepts ".", "$", etc., but that only works for the current buffer.
1067  * Returns -1 on error.
1068  */
1069  linenr_T
1070 tv_get_lnum(typval_T *argvars)
1071 {
1072  linenr_T lnum;
1073 
1074  lnum = (linenr_T)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[0], NULL);
1075  if (lnum == 0) // no valid number, try using arg like line()
1076  {
1077  int fnum;
1078  pos_T *fp = var2fpos(&argvars[0], TRUE, &fnum);
1079 
1080  if (fp != NULL)
1081  lnum = fp->lnum;
1082  }
1083  return lnum;
1084 }
1085 
1086 /*
1087  * Get the lnum from the first argument.
1088  * Also accepts "$", then "buf" is used.
1089  * Returns 0 on error.
1090  */
1091  linenr_T
1092 tv_get_lnum_buf(typval_T *argvars, buf_T *buf)
1093 {
1094  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_STRING
1095  && argvars[0].vval.v_string != NULL
1096  && argvars[0].vval.v_string[0] == '$'
1097  && buf != NULL)
1098  return buf->b_ml.ml_line_count;
1099  return (linenr_T)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[0], NULL);
1100 }

1102 #ifdef FEAT_FLOAT
1103 /*
1104  * Get the float value of "argvars[0]" into "f".
1105  * Returns FAIL when the argument is not a Number or Float.
1106  */
1107  static int
1108 get_float_arg(typval_T *argvars, float_T *f)
1109 {
1110  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_FLOAT)
1111  {
1112  *f = argvars[0].vval.v_float;
1113  return OK;
1114  }
1115  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_NUMBER)
1116  {
1117  *f = (float_T)argvars[0].vval.v_number;
1118  return OK;
1119  }
1120  emsg(_("E808: Number or Float required"));
1121  return FAIL;
1122 }

1124 /*
1125  * "abs(expr)" function
1126  */
1127  static void
1128 f_abs(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
1129 {
1130  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_FLOAT)
1131  {
1132  rettv->v_type = VAR_FLOAT;
1133  rettv->vval.v_float = fabs(argvars[0].vval.v_float);
1134  }
1135  else
1136  {
1137  varnumber_T n;
1138  int error = FALSE;
1139 
1140  n = tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[0], &error);
1141  if (error)
1142  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
1143  else if (n > 0)
1144  rettv->vval.v_number = n;
1145  else
1146  rettv->vval.v_number = -n;
1147  }
1148 }

1163 }

1173  & tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], NULL);

1227 #ifdef FEAT_BEVAL
1228  static void
1229 f_balloon_gettext(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)

1234  if (balloonEval->msg == NULL)

1241  static void
1242 f_balloon_show(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv UNUSED)
1243 {
1244  if (balloonEval != NULL)
1245  {
1246  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_LIST
1247 # ifdef FEAT_GUI
1248  && !gui.in_use
1249 # endif
1250  )
1251  {
1252  list_T *l = argvars[0].vval.v_list;
1253 
1254  // empty list removes the balloon
1255  post_balloon(balloonEval, NULL,
1256  l == NULL || l->lv_len == 0 ? NULL : l);
1257  }
1258  else
1259  {
1260  char_u *mesg = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
1261 
1262  if (mesg != NULL)
1263  // empty string removes the balloon
1264  post_balloon(balloonEval, *mesg == NUL ? NULL : mesg, NULL);
1265  }
1266  }
1267 }
1268 
1269 # if defined(FEAT_BEVAL_TERM)
1270  static void
1271 f_balloon_split(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv UNUSED)
1272 {
1273  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == OK)
1274  {
1275  char_u *msg = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
1276 
1277  if (msg != NULL)
1278  {
1279  pumitem_T *array;
1280  int size = split_message(msg, &array);
1281  int i;
1282 
1283  /* Skip the first and last item, they are always empty. */
1284  for (i = 1; i < size - 1; ++i)
1285  list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list, array[i].pum_text, -1);
1286  while (size > 0)
1287  vim_free(array[--size].pum_text);
1288  vim_free(array);
1289  }
1290  }
1291 }
1292 # endif
1293 #endif

1295 /*
1296  * Get buffer by number or pattern.
1297  */
1298  buf_T *
1299 tv_get_buf(typval_T *tv, int curtab_only)
1300 {
1301  char_u *name = tv->vval.v_string;
1302  buf_T *buf;
1303 
1304  if (tv->v_type == VAR_NUMBER)
1305  return buflist_findnr((int)tv->vval.v_number);
1306  if (tv->v_type != VAR_STRING)
1307  return NULL;
1308  if (name == NULL || *name == NUL)
1309  return curbuf;
1310  if (name[0] == '$' && name[1] == NUL)
1311  return lastbuf;
1312 
1313  buf = buflist_find_by_name(name, curtab_only);
1314 
1315  /* If not found, try expanding the name, like done for bufexists(). */
1316  if (buf == NULL)
1317  buf = find_buffer(tv);
1318 
1319  return buf;
1320 }
1321 
1322 /*
1323  * Get the buffer from "arg" and give an error and return NULL if it is not
1324  * valid.
1325  */
1326  buf_T *
1327 get_buf_arg(typval_T *arg)
1328 {
1329  buf_T *buf;
1330 
1331  ++emsg_off;
1332  buf = tv_get_buf(arg, FALSE);
1333  --emsg_off;
1334  if (buf == NULL)
1335  semsg(_("E158: Invalid buffer name: %s"), tv_get_string(arg));
1336  return buf;
1337 }

1339 /*
1340  * "byte2line(byte)" function
1341  */
1342  static void
1343 f_byte2line(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
1344 {
1345 #ifndef FEAT_BYTEOFF
1346  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
1347 #else
1348  long boff = 0;
1349 
1350  boff = tv_get_number(&argvars[0]) - 1; /* boff gets -1 on type error */
1351  if (boff < 0)
1352  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
1353  else
1354  rettv->vval.v_number = ml_find_line_or_offset(curbuf,
1355  (linenr_T)0, &boff);
1356 #endif
1357 }
1358 
1359  static void
1360 byteidx(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv, int comp UNUSED)
1361 {
1362  char_u *t;
1363  char_u *str;
1364  varnumber_T idx;
1365 
1366  str = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
1367  idx = tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], NULL);
1368  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
1369  if (str == NULL || idx < 0)
1370  return;
1371 
1372  t = str;
1373  for ( ; idx > 0; idx--)
1374  {
1375  if (*t == NUL) /* EOL reached */
1376  return;
1377  if (enc_utf8 && comp)
1378  t += utf_ptr2len(t);
1379  else
1380  t += (*mb_ptr2len)(t);
1381  }
1382  rettv->vval.v_number = (varnumber_T)(t - str);
1383 }

1403 /*
1404  * "call(func, arglist [, dict])" function
1405  */
1406  static void
1407 f_call(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
1408 {
1409  char_u *func;
1410  partial_T *partial = NULL;
1411  dict_T *selfdict = NULL;
1412 
1413  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_LIST)
1414  {
1415  emsg(_(e_listreq));
1416  return;
1417  }
1418  if (argvars[1].vval.v_list == NULL)
1419  return;
1420 
1421  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_FUNC)
1422  func = argvars[0].vval.v_string;
1423  else if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_PARTIAL)
1424  {
1425  partial = argvars[0].vval.v_partial;
1426  func = partial_name(partial);
1427  }
1428  else
1429  func = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
1430  if (*func == NUL)
1431  return; /* type error or empty name */
1432 
1433  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
1434  {
1435  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_DICT)
1436  {
1437  emsg(_(e_dictreq));
1438  return;
1439  }
1440  selfdict = argvars[2].vval.v_dict;
1441  }
1442 
1443  (void)func_call(func, &argvars[1], partial, selfdict, rettv);
1444 }

1534 /*
1535  * "col(string)" function
1536  */
1537  static void
1538 f_col(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
1539 {
1540  colnr_T col = 0;
1541  pos_T *fp;
1542  int fnum = curbuf->b_fnum;
1543 
1544  fp = var2fpos(&argvars[0], FALSE, &fnum);
1545  if (fp != NULL && fnum == curbuf->b_fnum)
1546  {
1547  if (fp->col == MAXCOL)
1548  {
1549  /* '> can be MAXCOL, get the length of the line then */
1550  if (fp->lnum <= curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count)
1551  col = (colnr_T)STRLEN(ml_get(fp->lnum)) + 1;
1552  else
1553  col = MAXCOL;
1554  }
1555  else
1556  {
1557  col = fp->col + 1;
1558  /* col(".") when the cursor is on the NUL at the end of the line
1559  * because of "coladd" can be seen as an extra column. */
1560  if (virtual_active() && fp == &curwin->w_cursor)
1561  {
1562  char_u *p = ml_get_cursor();
1563 
1564  if (curwin->w_cursor.coladd >= (colnr_T)chartabsize(p,
1565  curwin->w_virtcol - curwin->w_cursor.coladd))
1566  {
1567  int l;
1568 
1569  if (*p != NUL && p[(l = (*mb_ptr2len)(p))] == NUL)
1570  col += l;
1571  }
1572  }
1573  }
1574  }
1575  rettv->vval.v_number = col;
1576 }

1578 /*
1579  * "confirm(message, buttons[, default [, type]])" function
1580  */
1581  static void
1582 f_confirm(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv UNUSED)
1583 {
1584 #if defined(FEAT_GUI_DIALOG) || defined(FEAT_CON_DIALOG)
1585  char_u *message;
1586  char_u *buttons = NULL;
1587  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN];
1588  char_u buf2[NUMBUFLEN];
1589  int def = 1;
1590  int type = VIM_GENERIC;
1591  char_u *typestr;
1592  int error = FALSE;
1593 
1594  message = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
1595  if (message == NULL)
1596  error = TRUE;
1597  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
1598  {
1599  buttons = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[1], buf);
1600  if (buttons == NULL)
1601  error = TRUE;
1602  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
1603  {
1604  def = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &error);
1605  if (argvars[3].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
1606  {
1607  typestr = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[3], buf2);
1608  if (typestr == NULL)
1609  error = TRUE;
1610  else
1611  {
1612  switch (TOUPPER_ASC(*typestr))
1613  {
1614  case 'E': type = VIM_ERROR; break;
1615  case 'Q': type = VIM_QUESTION; break;
1616  case 'I': type = VIM_INFO; break;
1617  case 'W': type = VIM_WARNING; break;
1618  case 'G': type = VIM_GENERIC; break;
1619  }
1620  }
1621  }
1622  }
1623  }
1624 
1625  if (buttons == NULL || *buttons == NUL)
1626  buttons = (char_u *)_("&Ok");
1627 
1628  if (!error)
1629  rettv->vval.v_number = do_dialog(type, NULL, message, buttons,
1630  def, NULL, FALSE);
1631 #endif
1632 }

1675 /*
1676  * "cursor(lnum, col)" function, or
1677  * "cursor(list)"
1678  *
1679  * Moves the cursor to the specified line and column.
1680  * Returns 0 when the position could be set, -1 otherwise.
1681  */
1682  static void
1683 f_cursor(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
1684 {
1685  long line, col;
1686  long coladd = 0;
1687  int set_curswant = TRUE;
1688 
1689  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
1690  if (argvars[1].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
1691  {
1692  pos_T pos;
1693  colnr_T curswant = -1;
1694 
1695  if (list2fpos(argvars, &pos, NULL, &curswant) == FAIL)
1696  {
1697  emsg(_(e_invarg));
1698  return;
1699  }
1700  line = pos.lnum;
1701  col = pos.col;
1702  coladd = pos.coladd;
1703  if (curswant >= 0)
1704  {
1705  curwin->w_curswant = curswant - 1;
1706  set_curswant = FALSE;
1707  }
1708  }
1709  else
1710  {
1711  line = tv_get_lnum(argvars);
1712  col = (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], NULL);
1713  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
1714  coladd = (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], NULL);
1715  }
1716  if (line < 0 || col < 0 || coladd < 0)
1717  return; /* type error; errmsg already given */
1718  if (line > 0)
1719  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = line;
1720  if (col > 0)
1721  curwin->w_cursor.col = col - 1;
1722  curwin->w_cursor.coladd = coladd;
1723 
1724  /* Make sure the cursor is in a valid position. */
1725  check_cursor();
1726  /* Correct cursor for multi-byte character. */
1727  if (has_mbyte)
1728  mb_adjust_cursor();
1729 
1730  curwin->w_set_curswant = set_curswant;
1731  rettv->vval.v_number = 0;
1732 }
1733 
1734 #ifdef MSWIN
1735 /*
1736  * "debugbreak()" function
1737  */
1738  static void
1739 f_debugbreak(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
1740 {
1741  int pid;
1742 
1743  rettv->vval.v_number = FAIL;
1744  pid = (int)tv_get_number(&argvars[0]);
1745  if (pid == 0)
1746  emsg(_(e_invarg));
1747  else
1748  {
1749  HANDLE hProcess = OpenProcess(PROCESS_ALL_ACCESS, 0, pid);
1750 
1751  if (hProcess != NULL)
1752  {
1753  DebugBreakProcess(hProcess);
1754  CloseHandle(hProcess);
1755  rettv->vval.v_number = OK;
1756  }
1757  }
1758 }
1759 #endif

1790 /*
1791  * "empty({expr})" function
1792  */
1793  static void
1794 f_empty(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
1795 {
1796  int n = FALSE;
1797 
1798  switch (argvars[0].v_type)
1799  {
1800  case VAR_STRING:
1801  case VAR_FUNC:
1802  n = argvars[0].vval.v_string == NULL
1803  || *argvars[0].vval.v_string == NUL;
1804  break;
1805  case VAR_PARTIAL:
1806  n = FALSE;
1807  break;
1808  case VAR_NUMBER:
1809  n = argvars[0].vval.v_number == 0;
1810  break;
1811  case VAR_FLOAT:
1812 #ifdef FEAT_FLOAT
1813  n = argvars[0].vval.v_float == 0.0;
1814  break;
1815 #endif
1816  case VAR_LIST:
1817  n = argvars[0].vval.v_list == NULL
1818  || argvars[0].vval.v_list->lv_first == NULL;
1819  break;
1820  case VAR_DICT:
1821  n = argvars[0].vval.v_dict == NULL
1822  || argvars[0].vval.v_dict->dv_hashtab.ht_used == 0;
1823  break;
1824  case VAR_SPECIAL:
1825  n = argvars[0].vval.v_number != VVAL_TRUE;
1826  break;
1827 
1828  case VAR_BLOB:
1829  n = argvars[0].vval.v_blob == NULL
1830  || argvars[0].vval.v_blob->bv_ga.ga_len == 0;
1831  break;
1832 
1833  case VAR_JOB:
1834 #ifdef FEAT_JOB_CHANNEL
1835  n = argvars[0].vval.v_job == NULL
1836  || argvars[0].vval.v_job->jv_status != JOB_STARTED;
1837  break;
1838 #endif
1839  case VAR_CHANNEL:
1840 #ifdef FEAT_JOB_CHANNEL
1841  n = argvars[0].vval.v_channel == NULL
1842  || !channel_is_open(argvars[0].vval.v_channel);
1843  break;
1844 #endif
1845  case VAR_UNKNOWN:
1846  internal_error("f_empty(UNKNOWN)");
1847  n = TRUE;
1848  break;
1849  }
1850 
1851  rettv->vval.v_number = n;
1852 }
1853 
1854 /*
1855  * "environ()" function
1856  */
1857  static void
1858 f_environ(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
1859 {
1860 #if !defined(AMIGA)
1861  int i = 0;
1862  char_u *entry, *value;
1863 # ifdef MSWIN
1864  extern wchar_t **_wenviron;
1865 # else
1866  extern char **environ;
1867 # endif
1868 
1869  if (rettv_dict_alloc(rettv) != OK)
1870  return;
1871 
1872 # ifdef MSWIN
1873  if (*_wenviron == NULL)
1874  return;
1875 # else
1876  if (*environ == NULL)
1877  return;
1878 # endif
1879 
1880  for (i = 0; ; ++i)
1881  {
1882 # ifdef MSWIN
1883  short_u *p;
1884 
1885  if ((p = (short_u *)_wenviron[i]) == NULL)
1886  return;
1887  entry = utf16_to_enc(p, NULL);
1888 # else
1889  if ((entry = (char_u *)environ[i]) == NULL)
1890  return;
1891  entry = vim_strsave(entry);
1892 # endif
1893  if (entry == NULL) // out of memory
1894  return;
1895  if ((value = vim_strchr(entry, '=')) == NULL)
1896  {
1897  vim_free(entry);
1898  continue;
1899  }
1900  *value++ = NUL;
1901  dict_add_string(rettv->vval.v_dict, (char *)entry, value);
1902  vim_free(entry);
1903  }
1904 #endif
1905 }

1914

1916  tv_get_string_buf(&argvars[1], buf));
1917  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
1918 }

1920 /*
1921  * "eval()" function
1922  */
1923  static void
1924 f_eval(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
1925 {
1926  char_u *s, *p;
1927 
1928  s = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
1929  if (s != NULL)
1930  s = skipwhite(s);
1931 
1932  p = s;
1933  if (s == NULL || eval1(&s, rettv, TRUE) == FAIL)
1934  {
1935  if (p != NULL && !aborting())
1936  semsg(_(e_invexpr2), p);
1937  need_clr_eos = FALSE;
1938  rettv->v_type = VAR_NUMBER;
1939  rettv->vval.v_number = 0;
1940  }
1941  else if (*s != NUL)
1942  emsg(_(e_trailing));
1943 }

1954 static garray_T redir_execute_ga;
1955 
1956 /*
1957  * Append "value[value_len]" to the execute() output.
1958  */
1959  void
1960 execute_redir_str(char_u *value, int value_len)
1961 {
1962  int len;
1963 
1964  if (value_len == -1)
1965  len = (int)STRLEN(value); /* Append the entire string */
1966  else
1967  len = value_len; /* Append only "value_len" characters */
1968  if (ga_grow(&redir_execute_ga, len) == OK)
1969  {
1970  mch_memmove((char *)redir_execute_ga.ga_data
1971  + redir_execute_ga.ga_len, value, len);
1972  redir_execute_ga.ga_len += len;
1973  }
1974 }
1975 
1976 /*
1977  * Get next line from a list.
1978  * Called by do_cmdline() to get the next line.
1979  * Returns allocated string, or NULL for end of function.
1980  */
1981 
1982  static char_u *
1983 get_list_line(
1984  int c UNUSED,
1985  void *cookie,
1986  int indent UNUSED,
1987  int do_concat UNUSED)
1988 {
1989  listitem_T **p = (listitem_T **)cookie;
1990  listitem_T *item = *p;
1991  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN];
1992  char_u *s;
1993 
1994  if (item == NULL)
1995  return NULL;
1996  s = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&item->li_tv, buf);
1997  *p = item->li_next;
1998  return s == NULL ? NULL : vim_strsave(s);
1999 }
2000 
2001 /*
2002  * "execute()" function
2003  */
2004  void
2005 execute_common(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv, int arg_off)
2006 {
2007  char_u *cmd = NULL;
2008  list_T *list = NULL;
2009  int save_msg_silent = msg_silent;
2010  int save_emsg_silent = emsg_silent;
2011  int save_emsg_noredir = emsg_noredir;
2012  int save_redir_execute = redir_execute;
2013  int save_redir_off = redir_off;
2014  garray_T save_ga;
2015  int save_msg_col = msg_col;
2016  int echo_output = FALSE;
2017 
2018  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
2019  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
2020 
2021  if (argvars[arg_off].v_type == VAR_LIST)
2022  {
2023  list = argvars[arg_off].vval.v_list;
2024  if (list == NULL || list->lv_first == NULL)
2025  /* empty list, no commands, empty output */
2026  return;
2027  ++list->lv_refcount;
2028  }
2029  else
2030  {
2031  cmd = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[arg_off]);
2032  if (cmd == NULL)
2033  return;
2034  }
2035 
2036  if (argvars[arg_off + 1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
2037  {
2038  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN];
2039  char_u *s = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[arg_off + 1], buf);
2040 
2041  if (s == NULL)
2042  return;
2043  if (*s == NUL)
2044  echo_output = TRUE;
2045  if (STRNCMP(s, "silent", 6) == 0)
2046  ++msg_silent;
2047  if (STRCMP(s, "silent!") == 0)
2048  {
2049  emsg_silent = TRUE;
2050  emsg_noredir = TRUE;
2051  }
2052  }
2053  else
2054  ++msg_silent;
2055 
2056  if (redir_execute)
2057  save_ga = redir_execute_ga;
2058  ga_init2(&redir_execute_ga, (int)sizeof(char), 500);
2059  redir_execute = TRUE;
2060  redir_off = FALSE;
2061  if (!echo_output)
2062  msg_col = 0; // prevent leading spaces
2063 
2064  if (cmd != NULL)
2065  do_cmdline_cmd(cmd);
2066  else
2067  {
2068  listitem_T *item = list->lv_first;
2069 
2070  do_cmdline(NULL, get_list_line, (void *)&item,
2071  DOCMD_NOWAIT|DOCMD_VERBOSE|DOCMD_REPEAT|DOCMD_KEYTYPED);
2072  --list->lv_refcount;
2073  }
2074 
2075  /* Need to append a NUL to the result. */
2076  if (ga_grow(&redir_execute_ga, 1) == OK)
2077  {
2078  ((char *)redir_execute_ga.ga_data)[redir_execute_ga.ga_len] = NUL;
2079  rettv->vval.v_string = redir_execute_ga.ga_data;
2080  }
2081  else
2082  {
2083  ga_clear(&redir_execute_ga);
2084  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
2085  }
2086  msg_silent = save_msg_silent;
2087  emsg_silent = save_emsg_silent;
2088  emsg_noredir = save_emsg_noredir;
2089 
2090  redir_execute = save_redir_execute;
2091  if (redir_execute)
2092  redir_execute_ga = save_ga;
2093  redir_off = save_redir_off;
2094 
2095  // "silent reg" or "silent echo x" leaves msg_col somewhere in the line.
2096  if (echo_output)
2097  // When not working silently: put it in column zero. A following
2098  // "echon" will overwrite the message, unavoidably.
2099  msg_col = 0;
2100  else
2101  // When working silently: Put it back where it was, since nothing
2102  // should have been written.
2103  msg_col = save_msg_col;
2104 }

2113 }

2115 /*
2116  * "exists()" function
2117  */
2118  static void
2119 f_exists(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
2120 {
2121  char_u *p;
2122  int n = FALSE;
2123 
2124  p = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
2125  if (*p == '$') /* environment variable */
2126  {
2127  /* first try "normal" environment variables (fast) */
2128  if (mch_getenv(p + 1) != NULL)
2129  n = TRUE;
2130  else
2131  {
2132  /* try expanding things like $VIM and ${HOME} */
2133  p = expand_env_save(p);
2134  if (p != NULL && *p != '$')
2135  n = TRUE;
2136  vim_free(p);
2137  }
2138  }
2139  else if (*p == '&' || *p == '+') /* option */
2140  {
2141  n = (get_option_tv(&p, NULL, TRUE) == OK);
2142  if (*skipwhite(p) != NUL)
2143  n = FALSE; /* trailing garbage */
2144  }
2145  else if (*p == '*') /* internal or user defined function */
2146  {
2147  n = function_exists(p + 1, FALSE);
2148  }
2149  else if (*p == ':')
2150  {
2151  n = cmd_exists(p + 1);
2152  }
2153  else if (*p == '#')
2154  {
2155  if (p[1] == '#')
2156  n = autocmd_supported(p + 2);
2157  else
2158  n = au_exists(p + 1);
2159  }
2160  else /* internal variable */
2161  {
2162  n = var_exists(p);
2163  }
2164 
2165  rettv->vval.v_number = n;
2166 }

2178  if (get_float_arg(argvars, &f) == OK)
2179  rettv->vval.v_float = exp(f);
2180  else
2181  rettv->vval.v_float = 0.0;
2182 }
2183 #endif

2185 /*
2186  * "expand()" function
2187  */
2188  static void
2189 f_expand(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
2190 {
2191  char_u *s;
2192  int len;
2193  char *errormsg;
2194  int options = WILD_SILENT|WILD_USE_NL|WILD_LIST_NOTFOUND;
2195  expand_T xpc;
2196  int error = FALSE;
2197  char_u *result;
2198 
2199  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
2200  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN
2201  && argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN
2202  && tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &error)
2203  && !error)
2204  rettv_list_set(rettv, NULL);
2205 
2206  s = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
2207  if (*s == '%' || *s == '#' || *s == '<')
2208  {
2209  ++emsg_off;
2210  result = eval_vars(s, s, &len, NULL, &errormsg, NULL);
2211  --emsg_off;
2212  if (rettv->v_type == VAR_LIST)
2213  {
2214  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) != FAIL && result != NULL)
2215  list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list, result, -1);
2216  vim_free(result);
2217  }
2218  else
2219  rettv->vval.v_string = result;
2220  }
2221  else
2222  {
2223  /* When the optional second argument is non-zero, don't remove matches
2224  * for 'wildignore' and don't put matches for 'suffixes' at the end. */
2225  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN
2226  && tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error))
2227  options |= WILD_KEEP_ALL;
2228  if (!error)
2229  {
2230  ExpandInit(&xpc);
2231  xpc.xp_context = EXPAND_FILES;
2232  if (p_wic)
2233  options += WILD_ICASE;
2234  if (rettv->v_type == VAR_STRING)
2235  rettv->vval.v_string = ExpandOne(&xpc, s, NULL,
2236  options, WILD_ALL);
2237  else if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) != FAIL)
2238  {
2239  int i;
2240 
2241  ExpandOne(&xpc, s, NULL, options, WILD_ALL_KEEP);
2242  for (i = 0; i < xpc.xp_numfiles; i++)
2243  list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list, xpc.xp_files[i], -1);
2244  ExpandCleanup(&xpc);
2245  }
2246  }
2247  else
2248  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
2249  }
2250 }
2251 
2252 /*
2253  * "expandcmd()" function
2254  * Expand all the special characters in a command string.
2255  */
2256  static void
2257 f_expandcmd(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
2258 {
2259  exarg_T eap;
2260  char_u *cmdstr;
2261  char *errormsg = NULL;
2262 
2263  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
2264  cmdstr = vim_strsave(tv_get_string(&argvars[0]));
2265 
2266  memset(&eap, 0, sizeof(eap));
2267  eap.cmd = cmdstr;
2268  eap.arg = cmdstr;
2269  eap.argt |= EX_NOSPC;
2270  eap.usefilter = FALSE;
2271  eap.nextcmd = NULL;
2272  eap.cmdidx = CMD_USER;
2273 
2274  expand_filename(&eap, &cmdstr, &errormsg);
2275  if (errormsg != NULL && *errormsg != NUL)
2276  emsg(errormsg);
2277 
2278  rettv->vval.v_string = cmdstr;
2279 }

2281 /*
2282  * "feedkeys()" function
2283  */
2284  static void
2285 f_feedkeys(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv UNUSED)
2286 {
2287  int remap = TRUE;
2288  int insert = FALSE;
2289  char_u *keys, *flags;
2290  char_u nbuf[NUMBUFLEN];
2291  int typed = FALSE;
2292  int execute = FALSE;
2293  int dangerous = FALSE;
2294  int lowlevel = FALSE;
2295  char_u *keys_esc;
2296 
2297  /* This is not allowed in the sandbox. If the commands would still be
2298  * executed in the sandbox it would be OK, but it probably happens later,
2299  * when "sandbox" is no longer set. */
2300  if (check_secure())
2301  return;
2302 
2303  keys = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
2304 
2305  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
2306  {
2307  flags = tv_get_string_buf(&argvars[1], nbuf);
2308  for ( ; *flags != NUL; ++flags)
2309  {
2310  switch (*flags)
2311  {
2312  case 'n': remap = FALSE; break;
2313  case 'm': remap = TRUE; break;
2314  case 't': typed = TRUE; break;
2315  case 'i': insert = TRUE; break;
2316  case 'x': execute = TRUE; break;
2317  case '!': dangerous = TRUE; break;
2318  case 'L': lowlevel = TRUE; break;
2319  }
2320  }
2321  }
2322 
2323  if (*keys != NUL || execute)
2324  {
2325  /* Need to escape K_SPECIAL and CSI before putting the string in the
2326  * typeahead buffer. */
2327  keys_esc = vim_strsave_escape_csi(keys);
2328  if (keys_esc != NULL)
2329  {
2330  if (lowlevel)
2331  {
2332 #ifdef USE_INPUT_BUF
2333  add_to_input_buf(keys, (int)STRLEN(keys));
2334 #else
2335  emsg(_("E980: lowlevel input not supported"));
2336 #endif
2337  }
2338  else
2339  {
2340  ins_typebuf(keys_esc, (remap ? REMAP_YES : REMAP_NONE),
2341  insert ? 0 : typebuf.tb_len, !typed, FALSE);
2342  if (vgetc_busy
2343 #ifdef FEAT_TIMERS
2344  || timer_busy
2345 #endif
2346  )
2347  typebuf_was_filled = TRUE;
2348  }
2349  vim_free(keys_esc);
2350 
2351  if (execute)
2352  {
2353  int save_msg_scroll = msg_scroll;
2354 
2355  /* Avoid a 1 second delay when the keys start Insert mode. */
2356  msg_scroll = FALSE;
2357 
2358  if (!dangerous)
2359  ++ex_normal_busy;
2360  exec_normal(TRUE, lowlevel, TRUE);
2361  if (!dangerous)
2362  --ex_normal_busy;
2363 
2364  msg_scroll |= save_msg_scroll;
2365  }
2366  }
2367  }
2368 }

2372  * "float2nr({float})" function
2373  */
2374  static void
2375 f_float2nr(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)

2384  rettv->vval.v_number = VARNUM_MAX;
2385  else
2386  rettv->vval.v_number = (varnumber_T)f;
2387  }

2451  static void
2452 common_function(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv, int is_funcref)
2453 {
2454  char_u *s;
2455  char_u *name;
2456  int use_string = FALSE;
2457  partial_T *arg_pt = NULL;
2458  char_u *trans_name = NULL;
2459 
2460  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_FUNC)
2461  {
2462  /* function(MyFunc, [arg], dict) */
2463  s = argvars[0].vval.v_string;
2464  }
2465  else if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_PARTIAL
2466  && argvars[0].vval.v_partial != NULL)
2467  {
2468  /* function(dict.MyFunc, [arg]) */
2469  arg_pt = argvars[0].vval.v_partial;
2470  s = partial_name(arg_pt);
2471  }
2472  else
2473  {
2474  /* function('MyFunc', [arg], dict) */
2475  s = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
2476  use_string = TRUE;
2477  }
2478 
2479  if ((use_string && vim_strchr(s, AUTOLOAD_CHAR) == NULL) || is_funcref)
2480  {
2481  name = s;
2482  trans_name = trans_function_name(&name, FALSE,
2483  TFN_INT | TFN_QUIET | TFN_NO_AUTOLOAD | TFN_NO_DEREF, NULL, NULL);
2484  if (*name != NUL)
2485  s = NULL;
2486  }
2487 
2488  if (s == NULL || *s == NUL || (use_string && VIM_ISDIGIT(*s))
2489  || (is_funcref && trans_name == NULL))
2490  semsg(_(e_invarg2), use_string ? tv_get_string(&argvars[0]) : s);
2491  /* Don't check an autoload name for existence here. */
2492  else if (trans_name != NULL && (is_funcref
2493  ? find_func(trans_name) == NULL
2494  : !translated_function_exists(trans_name)))
2495  semsg(_("E700: Unknown function: %s"), s);
2496  else
2497  {
2498  int dict_idx = 0;
2499  int arg_idx = 0;
2500  list_T *list = NULL;
2501 
2502  if (STRNCMP(s, "s:", 2) == 0 || STRNCMP(s, "<SID>", 5) == 0)
2503  {
2504  char sid_buf[25];
2505  int off = *s == 's' ? 2 : 5;
2506 
2507  /* Expand s: and <SID> into <SNR>nr_, so that the function can
2508  * also be called from another script. Using trans_function_name()
2509  * would also work, but some plugins depend on the name being
2510  * printable text. */
2511  sprintf(sid_buf, "<SNR>%ld_", (long)current_sctx.sc_sid);
2512  name = alloc(STRLEN(sid_buf) + STRLEN(s + off) + 1);
2513  if (name != NULL)
2514  {
2515  STRCPY(name, sid_buf);
2516  STRCAT(name, s + off);
2517  }
2518  }
2519  else
2520  name = vim_strsave(s);
2521 
2522  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
2523  {
2524  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
2525  {
2526  /* function(name, [args], dict) */
2527  arg_idx = 1;
2528  dict_idx = 2;
2529  }
2530  else if (argvars[1].v_type == VAR_DICT)
2531  /* function(name, dict) */
2532  dict_idx = 1;
2533  else
2534  /* function(name, [args]) */
2535  arg_idx = 1;
2536  if (dict_idx > 0)
2537  {
2538  if (argvars[dict_idx].v_type != VAR_DICT)
2539  {
2540  emsg(_("E922: expected a dict"));
2541  vim_free(name);
2542  goto theend;
2543  }
2544  if (argvars[dict_idx].vval.v_dict == NULL)
2545  dict_idx = 0;
2546  }
2547  if (arg_idx > 0)
2548  {
2549  if (argvars[arg_idx].v_type != VAR_LIST)
2550  {
2551  emsg(_("E923: Second argument of function() must be a list or a dict"));
2552  vim_free(name);
2553  goto theend;
2554  }
2555  list = argvars[arg_idx].vval.v_list;
2556  if (list == NULL || list->lv_len == 0)
2557  arg_idx = 0;
2558  }
2559  }
2560  if (dict_idx > 0 || arg_idx > 0 || arg_pt != NULL || is_funcref)
2561  {
2562  partial_T *pt = ALLOC_CLEAR_ONE(partial_T);
2563 
2564  /* result is a VAR_PARTIAL */
2565  if (pt == NULL)
2566  vim_free(name);
2567  else
2568  {
2569  if (arg_idx > 0 || (arg_pt != NULL && arg_pt->pt_argc > 0))
2570  {
2571  listitem_T *li;
2572  int i = 0;
2573  int arg_len = 0;
2574  int lv_len = 0;
2575 
2576  if (arg_pt != NULL)
2577  arg_len = arg_pt->pt_argc;
2578  if (list != NULL)
2579  lv_len = list->lv_len;
2580  pt->pt_argc = arg_len + lv_len;
2581  pt->pt_argv = ALLOC_MULT(typval_T, pt->pt_argc);
2582  if (pt->pt_argv == NULL)
2583  {
2584  vim_free(pt);
2585  vim_free(name);
2586  goto theend;
2587  }
2588  for (i = 0; i < arg_len; i++)
2589  copy_tv(&arg_pt->pt_argv[i], &pt->pt_argv[i]);
2590  if (lv_len > 0)
2591  for (li = list->lv_first; li != NULL;
2592  li = li->li_next)
2593  copy_tv(&li->li_tv, &pt->pt_argv[i++]);
2594  }
2595 
2596  /* For "function(dict.func, [], dict)" and "func" is a partial
2597  * use "dict". That is backwards compatible. */
2598  if (dict_idx > 0)
2599  {
2600  /* The dict is bound explicitly, pt_auto is FALSE. */
2601  pt->pt_dict = argvars[dict_idx].vval.v_dict;
2602  ++pt->pt_dict->dv_refcount;
2603  }
2604  else if (arg_pt != NULL)
2605  {
2606  /* If the dict was bound automatically the result is also
2607  * bound automatically. */
2608  pt->pt_dict = arg_pt->pt_dict;
2609  pt->pt_auto = arg_pt->pt_auto;
2610  if (pt->pt_dict != NULL)
2611  ++pt->pt_dict->dv_refcount;
2612  }
2613 
2614  pt->pt_refcount = 1;
2615  if (arg_pt != NULL && arg_pt->pt_func != NULL)
2616  {
2617  pt->pt_func = arg_pt->pt_func;
2618  func_ptr_ref(pt->pt_func);
2619  vim_free(name);
2620  }
2621  else if (is_funcref)
2622  {
2623  pt->pt_func = find_func(trans_name);
2624  func_ptr_ref(pt->pt_func);
2625  vim_free(name);
2626  }
2627  else
2628  {
2629  pt->pt_name = name;
2630  func_ref(name);
2631  }
2632  }
2633  rettv->v_type = VAR_PARTIAL;
2634  rettv->vval.v_partial = pt;
2635  }
2636  else
2637  {
2638  /* result is a VAR_FUNC */
2639  rettv->v_type = VAR_FUNC;
2640  rettv->vval.v_string = name;
2641  func_ref(name);
2642  }
2643  }
2644 theend:
2645  vim_free(trans_name);
2646 }
2647

2649  * "funcref()" function
2650  */
2651  static void
2652 f_funcref(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
2653 {
2654  common_function(argvars, rettv, TRUE);
2655 }

2666 /*
2667  * "garbagecollect()" function
2668  */
2669  static void
2670 f_garbagecollect(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv UNUSED)
2671 {
2672  /* This is postponed until we are back at the toplevel, because we may be
2673  * using Lists and Dicts internally. E.g.: ":echo [garbagecollect()]". */
2674  want_garbage_collect = TRUE;
2675 
2676  if (argvars[0].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN && tv_get_number(&argvars[0]) == 1)
2677  garbage_collect_at_exit = TRUE;
2678 }
2679 
2680 /*
2681  * "get()" function
2682  */
2683  static void
2684 f_get(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
2685 {
2686  listitem_T *li;
2687  list_T *l;
2688  dictitem_T *di;
2689  dict_T *d;
2690  typval_T *tv = NULL;
2691  int what_is_dict = FALSE;
2692 
2693  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_BLOB)
2694  {
2695  int error = FALSE;
2696  int idx = tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error);
2697 
2698  if (!error)
2699  {
2700  rettv->v_type = VAR_NUMBER;
2701  if (idx < 0)
2702  idx = blob_len(argvars[0].vval.v_blob) + idx;
2703  if (idx < 0 || idx >= blob_len(argvars[0].vval.v_blob))
2704  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
2705  else
2706  {
2707  rettv->vval.v_number = blob_get(argvars[0].vval.v_blob, idx);
2708  tv = rettv;
2709  }
2710  }
2711  }
2712  else if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_LIST)
2713  {
2714  if ((l = argvars[0].vval.v_list) != NULL)
2715  {
2716  int error = FALSE;
2717 
2718  li = list_find(l, (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error));
2719  if (!error && li != NULL)
2720  tv = &li->li_tv;
2721  }
2722  }
2723  else if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_DICT)
2724  {
2725  if ((d = argvars[0].vval.v_dict) != NULL)
2726  {
2727  di = dict_find(d, tv_get_string(&argvars[1]), -1);
2728  if (di != NULL)
2729  tv = &di->di_tv;
2730  }
2731  }
2732  else if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_PARTIAL || argvars[0].v_type == VAR_FUNC)
2733  {
2734  partial_T *pt;
2735  partial_T fref_pt;
2736 
2737  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_PARTIAL)
2738  pt = argvars[0].vval.v_partial;
2739  else
2740  {
2741  vim_memset(&fref_pt, 0, sizeof(fref_pt));
2742  fref_pt.pt_name = argvars[0].vval.v_string;
2743  pt = &fref_pt;
2744  }
2745 
2746  if (pt != NULL)
2747  {
2748  char_u *what = tv_get_string(&argvars[1]);
2749  char_u *n;
2750 
2751  if (STRCMP(what, "func") == 0 || STRCMP(what, "name") == 0)
2752  {
2753  rettv->v_type = (*what == 'f' ? VAR_FUNC : VAR_STRING);
2754  n = partial_name(pt);
2755  if (n == NULL)
2756  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
2757  else
2758  {
2759  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strsave(n);
2760  if (rettv->v_type == VAR_FUNC)
2761  func_ref(rettv->vval.v_string);
2762  }
2763  }
2764  else if (STRCMP(what, "dict") == 0)
2765  {
2766  what_is_dict = TRUE;
2767  if (pt->pt_dict != NULL)
2768  rettv_dict_set(rettv, pt->pt_dict);
2769  }
2770  else if (STRCMP(what, "args") == 0)
2771  {
2772  rettv->v_type = VAR_LIST;
2773  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == OK)
2774  {
2775  int i;
2776 
2777  for (i = 0; i < pt->pt_argc; ++i)
2778  list_append_tv(rettv->vval.v_list, &pt->pt_argv[i]);
2779  }
2780  }
2781  else
2782  semsg(_(e_invarg2), what);
2783 
2784  // When {what} == "dict" and pt->pt_dict == NULL, evaluate the
2785  // third argument
2786  if (!what_is_dict)
2787  return;
2788  }
2789  }
2790  else
2791  semsg(_(e_listdictblobarg), "get()");
2792 
2793  if (tv == NULL)
2794  {
2795  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
2796  copy_tv(&argvars[2], rettv);
2797  }
2798  else
2799  copy_tv(tv, rettv);
2800 }

2802 /*
2803  * "getchangelist()" function
2804  */
2805  static void
2806 f_getchangelist(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
2807 {
2808 #ifdef FEAT_JUMPLIST
2809  buf_T *buf;
2810  int i;
2811  list_T *l;
2812  dict_T *d;
2813 #endif
2814 
2815  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) != OK)
2816  return;
2817 
2818 #ifdef FEAT_JUMPLIST
2819  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
2820  buf = curbuf;
2821  else
2822  {
2823  (void)tv_get_number(&argvars[0]); // issue errmsg if type error
2824  ++emsg_off;
2825  buf = tv_get_buf(&argvars[0], FALSE);
2826  --emsg_off;
2827  }
2828  if (buf == NULL)
2829  return;
2830 
2831  l = list_alloc();
2832  if (l == NULL)
2833  return;
2834 
2835  if (list_append_list(rettv->vval.v_list, l) == FAIL)
2836  return;
2837  /*
2838  * The current window change list index tracks only the position in the
2839  * current buffer change list. For other buffers, use the change list
2840  * length as the current index.
2841  */
2842  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list,
2843  (varnumber_T)((buf == curwin->w_buffer)
2844  ? curwin->w_changelistidx : buf->b_changelistlen));
2845 
2846  for (i = 0; i < buf->b_changelistlen; ++i)
2847  {
2848  if (buf->b_changelist[i].lnum == 0)
2849  continue;
2850  if ((d = dict_alloc()) == NULL)
2851  return;
2852  if (list_append_dict(l, d) == FAIL)
2853  return;
2854  dict_add_number(d, "lnum", (long)buf->b_changelist[i].lnum);
2855  dict_add_number(d, "col", (long)buf->b_changelist[i].col);
2856  dict_add_number(d, "coladd", (long)buf->b_changelist[i].coladd);
2857  }
2858 #endif
2859 }

3011  static void
3012 getpos_both(
3013  typval_T *argvars,
3014  typval_T *rettv,
3015  int getcurpos)
3016 {
3017  pos_T *fp;
3018  list_T *l;
3019  int fnum = -1;
3020 
3021  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == OK)
3022  {
3023  l = rettv->vval.v_list;
3024  if (getcurpos)
3025  fp = &curwin->w_cursor;
3026  else
3027  fp = var2fpos(&argvars[0], TRUE, &fnum);
3028  if (fnum != -1)
3029  list_append_number(l, (varnumber_T)fnum);
3030  else
3031  list_append_number(l, (varnumber_T)0);
3032  list_append_number(l, (fp != NULL) ? (varnumber_T)fp->lnum
3033  : (varnumber_T)0);
3034  list_append_number(l, (fp != NULL)
3035  ? (varnumber_T)(fp->col == MAXCOL ? MAXCOL : fp->col + 1)
3036  : (varnumber_T)0);
3037  list_append_number(l, (fp != NULL) ? (varnumber_T)fp->coladd :
3038  (varnumber_T)0);
3039  if (getcurpos)
3040  {
3041  int save_set_curswant = curwin->w_set_curswant;
3042  colnr_T save_curswant = curwin->w_curswant;
3043  colnr_T save_virtcol = curwin->w_virtcol;
3044 
3045  update_curswant();
3046  list_append_number(l, curwin->w_curswant == MAXCOL ?
3047  (varnumber_T)MAXCOL : (varnumber_T)curwin->w_curswant + 1);
3048 
3049  // Do not change "curswant", as it is unexpected that a get
3050  // function has a side effect.
3051  if (save_set_curswant)
3052  {
3053  curwin->w_set_curswant = save_set_curswant;
3054  curwin->w_curswant = save_curswant;
3055  curwin->w_virtcol = save_virtcol;
3056  curwin->w_valid &= ~VALID_VIRTCOL;
3057  }
3058  }
3059  }
3060  else
3061  rettv->vval.v_number = FALSE;
3062 }
3063

3065  * "getcurpos()" function
3066  */
3067  static void
3068 f_getcurpos(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
3069 {
3070  getpos_both(argvars, rettv, TRUE);
3071 }

3076  static void

3082 /*
3083  * "getreg()" function
3084  */
3085  static void
3086 f_getreg(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
3087 {
3088  char_u *strregname;
3089  int regname;
3090  int arg2 = FALSE;
3091  int return_list = FALSE;
3092  int error = FALSE;
3093 
3094  if (argvars[0].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
3095  {
3096  strregname = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
3097  error = strregname == NULL;
3098  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
3099  {
3100  arg2 = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error);
3101  if (!error && argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
3102  return_list = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &error);
3103  }
3104  }
3105  else
3106  strregname = get_vim_var_str(VV_REG);
3107 
3108  if (error)
3109  return;
3110 
3111  regname = (strregname == NULL ? '"' : *strregname);
3112  if (regname == 0)
3113  regname = '"';
3114 
3115  if (return_list)
3116  {
3117  rettv->v_type = VAR_LIST;
3118  rettv->vval.v_list = (list_T *)get_reg_contents(regname,
3119  (arg2 ? GREG_EXPR_SRC : 0) | GREG_LIST);
3120  if (rettv->vval.v_list == NULL)
3121  (void)rettv_list_alloc(rettv);
3122  else
3123  ++rettv->vval.v_list->lv_refcount;
3124  }
3125  else
3126  {
3127  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
3128  rettv->vval.v_string = get_reg_contents(regname,
3129  arg2 ? GREG_EXPR_SRC : 0);
3130  }
3131 }
3132 
3133 /*
3134  * "getregtype()" function
3135  */
3136  static void
3137 f_getregtype(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
3138 {
3139  char_u *strregname;
3140  int regname;
3141  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN + 2];
3142  long reglen = 0;
3143 
3144  if (argvars[0].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
3145  {
3146  strregname = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
3147  if (strregname == NULL) /* type error; errmsg already given */
3148  {
3149  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
3150  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
3151  return;
3152  }
3153  }
3154  else
3155  /* Default to v:register */
3156  strregname = get_vim_var_str(VV_REG);
3157 
3158  regname = (strregname == NULL ? '"' : *strregname);
3159  if (regname == 0)
3160  regname = '"';
3161 
3162  buf[0] = NUL;
3163  buf[1] = NUL;
3164  switch (get_reg_type(regname, &reglen))
3165  {
3166  case MLINE: buf[0] = 'V'; break;
3167  case MCHAR: buf[0] = 'v'; break;
3168  case MBLOCK:
3169  buf[0] = Ctrl_V;
3170  sprintf((char *)buf + 1, "%ld", reglen + 1);
3171  break;
3172  }
3173  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
3174  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strsave(buf);
3175 }

3703  NULL
3704  };
3705 
3706  name = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
3707  for (i = 0; has_list[i] != NULL; ++i)
3708  if (STRICMP(name, has_list[i]) == 0)
3709  {
3710  n = TRUE;
3711  break;
3712  }
3713 
3714  if (n == FALSE)
3715  {
3716  if (STRNICMP(name, "patch", 5) == 0)
3717  {
3718  if (name[5] == '-'
3719  && STRLEN(name) >= 11
3720  && vim_isdigit(name[6])
3721  && vim_isdigit(name[8])
3722  && vim_isdigit(name[10]))
3723  {
3724  int major = atoi((char *)name + 6);
3725  int minor = atoi((char *)name + 8);
3726 
3727  /* Expect "patch-9.9.01234". */
3728  n = (major < VIM_VERSION_MAJOR
3729  || (major == VIM_VERSION_MAJOR
3730  && (minor < VIM_VERSION_MINOR
3731  || (minor == VIM_VERSION_MINOR
3732  && has_patch(atoi((char *)name + 10))))));
3733  }
3734  else
3735  n = has_patch(atoi((char *)name + 5));
3736  }
3737  else if (STRICMP(name, "vim_starting") == 0)
3738  n = (starting != 0);
3739  else if (STRICMP(name, "ttyin") == 0)
3740  n = mch_input_isatty();
3741  else if (STRICMP(name, "ttyout") == 0)
3742  n = stdout_isatty;
3743  else if (STRICMP(name, "multi_byte_encoding") == 0)
3744  n = has_mbyte;
3745 #if defined(FEAT_BEVAL) && defined(FEAT_GUI_MSWIN)
3746  else if (STRICMP(name, "balloon_multiline") == 0)
3747  n = multiline_balloon_available();
3748 #endif
3749 #ifdef DYNAMIC_TCL
3750  else if (STRICMP(name, "tcl") == 0)
3751  n = tcl_enabled(FALSE);
3752 #endif
3753 #if defined(USE_ICONV) && defined(DYNAMIC_ICONV)
3754  else if (STRICMP(name, "iconv") == 0)
3755  n = iconv_enabled(FALSE);
3756 #endif
3757 #ifdef DYNAMIC_LUA
3758  else if (STRICMP(name, "lua") == 0)
3759  n = lua_enabled(FALSE);
3760 #endif
3761 #ifdef DYNAMIC_MZSCHEME
3762  else if (STRICMP(name, "mzscheme") == 0)
3763  n = mzscheme_enabled(FALSE);
3764 #endif
3765 #ifdef DYNAMIC_RUBY
3766  else if (STRICMP(name, "ruby") == 0)
3767  n = ruby_enabled(FALSE);
3768 #endif
3769 #ifdef DYNAMIC_PYTHON
3770  else if (STRICMP(name, "python") == 0)
3771  n = python_enabled(FALSE);
3772 #endif
3773 #ifdef DYNAMIC_PYTHON3
3774  else if (STRICMP(name, "python3") == 0)
3775  n = python3_enabled(FALSE);
3776 #endif
3777 #if defined(DYNAMIC_PYTHON) || defined(DYNAMIC_PYTHON3)
3778  else if (STRICMP(name, "pythonx") == 0)
3779  {
3780 # if defined(DYNAMIC_PYTHON) && defined(DYNAMIC_PYTHON3)
3781  if (p_pyx == 0)
3782  n = python3_enabled(FALSE) || python_enabled(FALSE);
3783  else if (p_pyx == 3)
3784  n = python3_enabled(FALSE);
3785  else if (p_pyx == 2)
3786  n = python_enabled(FALSE);
3787 # elif defined(DYNAMIC_PYTHON)
3788  n = python_enabled(FALSE);
3789 # elif defined(DYNAMIC_PYTHON3)
3790  n = python3_enabled(FALSE);
3791 # endif
3792  }
3793 #endif
3794 #ifdef DYNAMIC_PERL
3795  else if (STRICMP(name, "perl") == 0)
3796  n = perl_enabled(FALSE);
3797 #endif
3798 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
3799  else if (STRICMP(name, "gui_running") == 0)
3800  n = (gui.in_use || gui.starting);
3801 # ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
3802  else if (STRICMP(name, "browse") == 0)
3803  n = gui.in_use; /* gui_mch_browse() works when GUI is running */
3804 # endif
3805 #endif
3806 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
3807  else if (STRICMP(name, "syntax_items") == 0)
3808  n = syntax_present(curwin);
3809 #endif
3810 #ifdef FEAT_VTP
3811  else if (STRICMP(name, "vcon") == 0)
3812  n = is_term_win32() && has_vtp_working();
3813 #endif
3814 #ifdef FEAT_NETBEANS_INTG
3815  else if (STRICMP(name, "netbeans_enabled") == 0)
3816  n = netbeans_active();
3817 #endif

3820  n = gpm_enabled();
3821 #endif

3824  n = terminal_enabled();
3825 #endif
3826 #if defined(FEAT_TERMINAL) && defined(MSWIN)

3828  n = use_conpty();
3829 #endif
3830 #ifdef FEAT_CLIPBOARD
3831  else if (STRICMP(name, "clipboard_working") == 0)
3832  n = clip_star.available;
3833 #endif
3834  }
3835 
3836  rettv->vval.v_number = n;
3837 }

3839 /*

3841  */
3842  static void
3843 f_haslocaldir(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
3844 {
3845  tabpage_T *tp = NULL;
3846  win_T *wp = NULL;
3847 
3848  wp = find_tabwin(&argvars[0], &argvars[1], &tp);
3849 
3850  // Check for window-local and tab-local directories
3851  if (wp != NULL && wp->w_localdir != NULL)
3852  rettv->vval.v_number = 1;
3853  else if (tp != NULL && tp->tp_localdir != NULL)
3854  rettv->vval.v_number = 2;
3855  else
3856  rettv->vval.v_number = 0;
3857 }

3864 {

3869

3871  if (argvars[1].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
3872  mode = (char_u *)"nvo";
3873  else
3874  {
3875  mode = tv_get_string_buf(&argvars[1], buf);
3876  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
3877  abbr = (int)tv_get_number(&argvars[2]);
3878  }
3879 
3880  if (map_to_exists(name, mode, abbr))
3881  rettv->vval.v_number = TRUE;
3882  else
3883  rettv->vval.v_number = FALSE;
3884 }

3917 /*
3918  * iconv() function
3919  */
3920  static void
3921 f_iconv(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
3922 {
3923  char_u buf1[NUMBUFLEN];
3924  char_u buf2[NUMBUFLEN];
3925  char_u *from, *to, *str;
3926  vimconv_T vimconv;
3927 
3928  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
3929  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
3930 
3931  str = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
3932  from = enc_canonize(enc_skip(tv_get_string_buf(&argvars[1], buf1)));
3933  to = enc_canonize(enc_skip(tv_get_string_buf(&argvars[2], buf2)));
3934  vimconv.vc_type = CONV_NONE;
3935  convert_setup(&vimconv, from, to);
3936 
3937  /* If the encodings are equal, no conversion needed. */
3938  if (vimconv.vc_type == CONV_NONE)
3939  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strsave(str);
3940  else
3941  rettv->vval.v_string = string_convert(&vimconv, str, NULL);
3942 
3943  convert_setup(&vimconv, NULL, NULL);
3944  vim_free(from);
3945  vim_free(to);
3946 }

3958  rettv->vval.v_number = get_indent_lnum(lnum);
3959  else
3960  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
3961 }
3962 
3963 /*
3964  * "index()" function
3965  */
3966  static void
3967 f_index(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
3968 {
3969  list_T *l;
3970  listitem_T *item;
3971  blob_T *b;
3972  long idx = 0;
3973  int ic = FALSE;
3974  int error = FALSE;
3975 
3976  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
3977  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_BLOB)
3978  {
3979  typval_T tv;
3980  int start = 0;
3981 
3982  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
3983  {
3984  start = tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &error);
3985  if (error)
3986  return;
3987  }
3988  b = argvars[0].vval.v_blob;
3989  if (b == NULL)
3990  return;
3991  if (start < 0)
3992  {
3993  start = blob_len(b) + start;
3994  if (start < 0)
3995  start = 0;
3996  }
3997 
3998  for (idx = start; idx < blob_len(b); ++idx)
3999  {
4000  tv.v_type = VAR_NUMBER;
4001  tv.vval.v_number = blob_get(b, idx);
4002  if (tv_equal(&tv, &argvars[1], ic, FALSE))
4003  {
4004  rettv->vval.v_number = idx;
4005  return;
4006  }
4007  }
4008  return;
4009  }
4010  else if (argvars[0].v_type != VAR_LIST)
4011  {
4012  emsg(_(e_listblobreq));
4013  return;
4014  }
4015 
4016  l = argvars[0].vval.v_list;
4017  if (l != NULL)
4018  {
4019  item = l->lv_first;
4020  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
4021  {
4022  /* Start at specified item. Use the cached index that list_find()
4023  * sets, so that a negative number also works. */
4024  item = list_find(l, (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &error));
4025  idx = l->lv_idx;
4026  if (argvars[3].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
4027  ic = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[3], &error);
4028  if (error)
4029  item = NULL;
4030  }
4031 
4032  for ( ; item != NULL; item = item->li_next, ++idx)
4033  if (tv_equal(&item->li_tv, &argvars[1], ic, FALSE))
4034  {
4035  rettv->vval.v_number = idx;
4036  break;
4037  }
4038  }
4039 }

4053 /*
4054  * "inputdialog()" function
4055  */
4056  static void
4057 f_inputdialog(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
4058 {
4059 #if defined(FEAT_GUI_TEXTDIALOG)
4060  /* Use a GUI dialog if the GUI is running and 'c' is not in 'guioptions' */
4061  if (gui.in_use && vim_strchr(p_go, GO_CONDIALOG) == NULL)
4062  {
4063  char_u *message;
4064  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN];
4065  char_u *defstr = (char_u *)"";
4066 
4067  message = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
4068  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN
4069  && (defstr = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[1], buf)) != NULL)
4070  vim_strncpy(IObuff, defstr, IOSIZE - 1);
4071  else
4072  IObuff[0] = NUL;
4073  if (message != NULL && defstr != NULL
4074  && do_dialog(VIM_QUESTION, NULL, message,
4075  (char_u *)_("&OK\n&Cancel"), 1, IObuff, FALSE) == 1)
4076  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strsave(IObuff);
4077  else
4078  {
4079  if (message != NULL && defstr != NULL
4080  && argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN
4081  && argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
4082  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strsave(
4083  tv_get_string_buf(&argvars[2], buf));
4084  else
4085  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
4086  }
4087  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
4088  }
4089  else
4090 #endif
4091  get_user_input(argvars, rettv, TRUE, inputsecret_flag);
4092 }

4094 /*
4095  * "inputlist()" function
4096  */
4097  static void
4098 f_inputlist(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
4099 {
4100  listitem_T *li;
4101  int selected;
4102  int mouse_used;
4103 
4104 #ifdef NO_CONSOLE_INPUT
4105  /* While starting up, there is no place to enter text. When running tests
4106  * with --not-a-term we assume feedkeys() will be used. */
4107  if (no_console_input() && !is_not_a_term())
4108  return;
4109 #endif
4110  if (argvars[0].v_type != VAR_LIST || argvars[0].vval.v_list == NULL)
4111  {
4112  semsg(_(e_listarg), "inputlist()");
4113  return;
4114  }
4115 
4116  msg_start();
4117  msg_row = Rows - 1; /* for when 'cmdheight' > 1 */
4118  lines_left = Rows; /* avoid more prompt */
4119  msg_scroll = TRUE;
4120  msg_clr_eos();
4121 
4122  for (li = argvars[0].vval.v_list->lv_first; li != NULL; li = li->li_next)
4123  {
4124  msg_puts((char *)tv_get_string(&li->li_tv));
4125  msg_putchar('\n');
4126  }
4127 
4128  /* Ask for choice. */
4129  selected = prompt_for_number(&mouse_used);
4130  if (mouse_used)
4131  selected -= lines_left;
4132 
4133  rettv->vval.v_number = selected;
4134 }

4136 static garray_T ga_userinput = {0, 0, sizeof(tasave_T), 4, NULL};
4137 
4138 /*
4139  * "inputrestore()" function
4140  */
4141  static void
4142 f_inputrestore(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
4143 {
4144  if (ga_userinput.ga_len > 0)
4145  {
4146  --ga_userinput.ga_len;
4147  restore_typeahead((tasave_T *)(ga_userinput.ga_data)
4148  + ga_userinput.ga_len);
4149  /* default return is zero == OK */
4150  }
4151  else if (p_verbose > 1)
4152  {
4153  verb_msg(_("called inputrestore() more often than inputsave()"));
4154  rettv->vval.v_number = 1; /* Failed */
4155  }
4156 }
4157 
4158 /*
4159  * "inputsave()" function
4160  */
4161  static void
4162 f_inputsave(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
4163 {
4164  /* Add an entry to the stack of typeahead storage. */
4165  if (ga_grow(&ga_userinput, 1) == OK)
4166  {
4167  save_typeahead((tasave_T *)(ga_userinput.ga_data)
4168  + ga_userinput.ga_len);
4169  ++ga_userinput.ga_len;
4170  /* default return is zero == OK */
4171  }
4172  else
4173  rettv->vval.v_number = 1; /* Failed */
4174 }

4198 /*
4199  * Return TRUE if typeval "tv" is locked: Either that value is locked itself
4200  * or it refers to a List or Dictionary that is locked.
4201  */
4202  static int
4203 tv_islocked(typval_T *tv)
4204 {
4205  return (tv->v_lock & VAR_LOCKED)
4206  || (tv->v_type == VAR_LIST
4207  && tv->vval.v_list != NULL
4208  && (tv->vval.v_list->lv_lock & VAR_LOCKED))
4209  || (tv->v_type == VAR_DICT
4210  && tv->vval.v_dict != NULL
4211  && (tv->vval.v_dict->dv_lock & VAR_LOCKED));
4212 }
4213 
4214 /*
4215  * "islocked()" function
4216  */
4217  static void
4218 f_islocked(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
4219 {
4220  lval_T lv;
4221  char_u *end;
4222  dictitem_T *di;
4223 
4224  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
4225  end = get_lval(tv_get_string(&argvars[0]), NULL, &lv, FALSE, FALSE,
4226  GLV_NO_AUTOLOAD | GLV_READ_ONLY, FNE_CHECK_START);
4227  if (end != NULL && lv.ll_name != NULL)
4228  {
4229  if (*end != NUL)
4230  emsg(_(e_trailing));
4231  else
4232  {
4233  if (lv.ll_tv == NULL)
4234  {
4235  di = find_var(lv.ll_name, NULL, TRUE);
4236  if (di != NULL)
4237  {
4238  /* Consider a variable locked when:
4239  * 1. the variable itself is locked
4240  * 2. the value of the variable is locked.
4241  * 3. the List or Dict value is locked.
4242  */
4243  rettv->vval.v_number = ((di->di_flags & DI_FLAGS_LOCK)
4244  || tv_islocked(&di->di_tv));
4245  }
4246  }
4247  else if (lv.ll_range)
4248  emsg(_("E786: Range not allowed"));
4249  else if (lv.ll_newkey != NULL)
4250  semsg(_(e_dictkey), lv.ll_newkey);
4251  else if (lv.ll_list != NULL)
4252  /* List item. */
4253  rettv->vval.v_number = tv_islocked(&lv.ll_li->li_tv);
4254  else
4255  /* Dictionary item. */
4256  rettv->vval.v_number = tv_islocked(&lv.ll_di->di_tv);
4257  }
4258  }
4259 
4260  clear_lval(&lv);
4261 }

4301 /*
4302  * "len()" function
4303  */
4304  static void
4305 f_len(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
4306 {

4308  {
4309  case VAR_STRING:
4310  case VAR_NUMBER:
4311  rettv->vval.v_number = (varnumber_T)STRLEN(
4312  tv_get_string(&argvars[0]));
4313  break;
4314  case VAR_BLOB:
4315  rettv->vval.v_number = blob_len(argvars[0].vval.v_blob);
4316  break;

4319  break;
4320  case VAR_DICT:
4321  rettv->vval.v_number = dict_len(argvars[0].vval.v_dict);
4322  break;
4323  case VAR_UNKNOWN:
4324  case VAR_SPECIAL:
4325  case VAR_FLOAT:
4326  case VAR_FUNC:
4327  case VAR_PARTIAL:
4328  case VAR_JOB:
4329  case VAR_CHANNEL:
4330  emsg(_("E701: Invalid type for len()"));
4331  break;
4332  }
4333 }

4335  static void
4336 libcall_common(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv, int type)
4337 {
4338 #ifdef FEAT_LIBCALL
4339  char_u *string_in;
4340  char_u **string_result;
4341  int nr_result;
4342 #endif
4343 
4344  rettv->v_type = type;
4345  if (type != VAR_NUMBER)
4346  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
4347 
4348  if (check_restricted() || check_secure())
4349  return;
4350 
4351 #ifdef FEAT_LIBCALL
4352  /* The first two args must be strings, otherwise it's meaningless */
4353  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_STRING && argvars[1].v_type == VAR_STRING)
4354  {
4355  string_in = NULL;
4356  if (argvars[2].v_type == VAR_STRING)
4357  string_in = argvars[2].vval.v_string;
4358  if (type == VAR_NUMBER)
4359  string_result = NULL;
4360  else
4361  string_result = &rettv->vval.v_string;
4362  if (mch_libcall(argvars[0].vval.v_string,
4363  argvars[1].vval.v_string,
4364  string_in,
4365  argvars[2].vval.v_number,
4366  string_result,
4367  &nr_result) == OK
4368  && type == VAR_NUMBER)
4369  rettv->vval.v_number = nr_result;
4370  }
4371 #endif
4372 }

4553 typedef enum
4554 {
4555  MATCH_END, /* matchend() */
4556  MATCH_MATCH, /* match() */
4557  MATCH_STR, /* matchstr() */
4558  MATCH_LIST, /* matchlist() */
4559  MATCH_POS /* matchstrpos() */
4560 } matchtype_T;
4561 
4562  static void
4563 find_some_match(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv, matchtype_T type)
4564 {
4565  char_u *str = NULL;
4566  long len = 0;
4567  char_u *expr = NULL;
4568  char_u *pat;
4569  regmatch_T regmatch;
4570  char_u patbuf[NUMBUFLEN];
4571  char_u strbuf[NUMBUFLEN];
4572  char_u *save_cpo;
4573  long start = 0;
4574  long nth = 1;
4575  colnr_T startcol = 0;
4576  int match = 0;
4577  list_T *l = NULL;
4578  listitem_T *li = NULL;
4579  long idx = 0;
4580  char_u *tofree = NULL;
4581 
4582  /* Make 'cpoptions' empty, the 'l' flag should not be used here. */
4583  save_cpo = p_cpo;
4584  p_cpo = (char_u *)"";
4585 
4586  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
4587  if (type == MATCH_LIST || type == MATCH_POS)
4588  {
4589  /* type MATCH_LIST: return empty list when there are no matches.
4590  * type MATCH_POS: return ["", -1, -1, -1] */
4591  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == FAIL)
4592  goto theend;
4593  if (type == MATCH_POS
4594  && (list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list,
4595  (char_u *)"", 0) == FAIL
4596  || list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list,
4597  (varnumber_T)-1) == FAIL
4598  || list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list,
4599  (varnumber_T)-1) == FAIL
4600  || list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list,
4601  (varnumber_T)-1) == FAIL))
4602  {
4603  list_free(rettv->vval.v_list);
4604  rettv->vval.v_list = NULL;
4605  goto theend;
4606  }
4607  }
4608  else if (type == MATCH_STR)
4609  {
4610  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
4611  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
4612  }
4613 
4614  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_LIST)
4615  {
4616  if ((l = argvars[0].vval.v_list) == NULL)
4617  goto theend;
4618  li = l->lv_first;
4619  }
4620  else
4621  {
4622  expr = str = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
4623  len = (long)STRLEN(str);
4624  }
4625 
4626  pat = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[1], patbuf);
4627  if (pat == NULL)
4628  goto theend;
4629 
4630  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
4631  {
4632  int error = FALSE;
4633 
4634  start = (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &error);
4635  if (error)
4636  goto theend;
4637  if (l != NULL)
4638  {
4639  li = list_find(l, start);
4640  if (li == NULL)
4641  goto theend;
4642  idx = l->lv_idx; /* use the cached index */
4643  }
4644  else
4645  {
4646  if (start < 0)
4647  start = 0;
4648  if (start > len)
4649  goto theend;
4650  /* When "count" argument is there ignore matches before "start",
4651  * otherwise skip part of the string. Differs when pattern is "^"
4652  * or "<". */
4653  if (argvars[3].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
4654  startcol = start;
4655  else
4656  {
4657  str += start;
4658  len -= start;
4659  }
4660  }
4661 
4662  if (argvars[3].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
4663  nth = (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[3], &error);
4664  if (error)
4665  goto theend;
4666  }
4667 
4668  regmatch.regprog = vim_regcomp(pat, RE_MAGIC + RE_STRING);
4669  if (regmatch.regprog != NULL)
4670  {
4671  regmatch.rm_ic = p_ic;
4672 
4673  for (;;)
4674  {
4675  if (l != NULL)
4676  {
4677  if (li == NULL)
4678  {
4679  match = FALSE;
4680  break;
4681  }
4682  vim_free(tofree);
4683  expr = str = echo_string(&li->li_tv, &tofree, strbuf, 0);
4684  if (str == NULL)
4685  break;
4686  }
4687 
4688  match = vim_regexec_nl(&regmatch, str, (colnr_T)startcol);
4689 
4690  if (match && --nth <= 0)
4691  break;
4692  if (l == NULL && !match)
4693  break;
4694 
4695  /* Advance to just after the match. */
4696  if (l != NULL)
4697  {
4698  li = li->li_next;
4699  ++idx;
4700  }
4701  else
4702  {
4703  startcol = (colnr_T)(regmatch.startp[0]
4704  + (*mb_ptr2len)(regmatch.startp[0]) - str);
4705  if (startcol > (colnr_T)len
4706  || str + startcol <= regmatch.startp[0])
4707  {
4708  match = FALSE;
4709  break;
4710  }
4711  }
4712  }
4713 
4714  if (match)
4715  {
4716  if (type == MATCH_POS)
4717  {
4718  listitem_T *li1 = rettv->vval.v_list->lv_first;
4719  listitem_T *li2 = li1->li_next;
4720  listitem_T *li3 = li2->li_next;
4721  listitem_T *li4 = li3->li_next;
4722 
4723  vim_free(li1->li_tv.vval.v_string);
4724  li1->li_tv.vval.v_string = vim_strnsave(regmatch.startp[0],
4725  (int)(regmatch.endp[0] - regmatch.startp[0]));
4726  li3->li_tv.vval.v_number =
4727  (varnumber_T)(regmatch.startp[0] - expr);
4728  li4->li_tv.vval.v_number =
4729  (varnumber_T)(regmatch.endp[0] - expr);
4730  if (l != NULL)
4731  li2->li_tv.vval.v_number = (varnumber_T)idx;
4732  }
4733  else if (type == MATCH_LIST)
4734  {
4735  int i;
4736 
4737  /* return list with matched string and submatches */
4738  for (i = 0; i < NSUBEXP; ++i)
4739  {
4740  if (regmatch.endp[i] == NULL)
4741  {
4742  if (list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list,
4743  (char_u *)"", 0) == FAIL)
4744  break;
4745  }
4746  else if (list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list,
4747  regmatch.startp[i],
4748  (int)(regmatch.endp[i] - regmatch.startp[i]))
4749  == FAIL)
4750  break;
4751  }
4752  }
4753  else if (type == MATCH_STR)
4754  {
4755  /* return matched string */
4756  if (l != NULL)
4757  copy_tv(&li->li_tv, rettv);
4758  else
4759  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strnsave(regmatch.startp[0],
4760  (int)(regmatch.endp[0] - regmatch.startp[0]));
4761  }
4762  else if (l != NULL)
4763  rettv->vval.v_number = idx;
4764  else
4765  {
4766  if (type != MATCH_END)
4767  rettv->vval.v_number =
4768  (varnumber_T)(regmatch.startp[0] - str);
4769  else
4770  rettv->vval.v_number =
4771  (varnumber_T)(regmatch.endp[0] - str);
4772  rettv->vval.v_number += (varnumber_T)(str - expr);
4773  }
4774  }
4775  vim_regfree(regmatch.regprog);
4776  }
4777 
4778 theend:
4779  if (type == MATCH_POS && l == NULL && rettv->vval.v_list != NULL)
4780  /* matchstrpos() without a list: drop the second item. */
4781  listitem_remove(rettv->vval.v_list,
4782  rettv->vval.v_list->lv_first->li_next);
4783  vim_free(tofree);
4784  p_cpo = save_cpo;
4785 }

4832  static void
4833 max_min(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv, int domax)
4834 {
4835  varnumber_T n = 0;
4836  varnumber_T i;
4837  int error = FALSE;
4838 
4839  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_LIST)
4840  {
4841  list_T *l;
4842  listitem_T *li;
4843 
4844  l = argvars[0].vval.v_list;
4845  if (l != NULL)
4846  {
4847  li = l->lv_first;
4848  if (li != NULL)
4849  {
4850  n = tv_get_number_chk(&li->li_tv, &error);
4851  for (;;)
4852  {
4853  li = li->li_next;
4854  if (li == NULL)
4855  break;
4856  i = tv_get_number_chk(&li->li_tv, &error);
4857  if (domax ? i > n : i < n)
4858  n = i;
4859  }
4860  }
4861  }
4862  }
4863  else if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_DICT)
4864  {
4865  dict_T *d;
4866  int first = TRUE;
4867  hashitem_T *hi;
4868  int todo;
4869 
4870  d = argvars[0].vval.v_dict;
4871  if (d != NULL)
4872  {
4873  todo = (int)d->dv_hashtab.ht_used;
4874  for (hi = d->dv_hashtab.ht_array; todo > 0; ++hi)
4875  {
4876  if (!HASHITEM_EMPTY(hi))
4877  {
4878  --todo;
4879  i = tv_get_number_chk(&HI2DI(hi)->di_tv, &error);
4880  if (first)
4881  {
4882  n = i;
4883  first = FALSE;
4884  }
4885  else if (domax ? i > n : i < n)
4886  n = i;
4887  }
4888  }
4889  }
4890  }
4891  else
4892  semsg(_(e_listdictarg), domax ? "max()" : "min()");
4893  rettv->vval.v_number = error ? 0 : n;
4894 }
4895 
4896 /*
4897  * "max()" function
4898  */
4899  static void
4900 f_max(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
4901 {
4902  max_min(argvars, rettv, TRUE);
4903 }

4909 f_min(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)

5059 /*
5060  * "printf()" function
5061  */
5062  static void
5063 f_printf(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
5064 {

5066  int len;
5067  char_u *s;

5069  char *fmt;
5070 
5071  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
5072  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
5073 
5074  /* Get the required length, allocate the buffer and do it for real. */
5075  did_emsg = FALSE;
5076  fmt = (char *)tv_get_string_buf(&argvars[0], buf);
5077  len = vim_vsnprintf_typval(NULL, 0, fmt, ap, argvars + 1);
5078  if (!did_emsg)
5079  {
5080  s = alloc(len + 1);
5081  if (s != NULL)
5082  {
5083  rettv->vval.v_string = s;
5084  (void)vim_vsnprintf_typval((char *)s, len + 1, fmt,
5085  ap, argvars + 1);
5086  }
5087  }
5088  did_emsg |= saved_did_emsg;
5089 }

5178 /*
5179  * "range()" function
5180  */
5181  static void
5182 f_range(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
5183 {
5184  varnumber_T start;
5185  varnumber_T end;
5186  varnumber_T stride = 1;
5187  varnumber_T i;
5188  int error = FALSE;
5189 
5190  start = tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[0], &error);
5191  if (argvars[1].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
5192  {
5193  end = start - 1;
5194  start = 0;
5195  }
5196  else
5197  {
5198  end = tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error);
5199  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
5200  stride = tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &error);
5201  }
5202 
5203  if (error)
5204  return; /* type error; errmsg already given */
5205  if (stride == 0)
5206  emsg(_("E726: Stride is zero"));
5207  else if (stride > 0 ? end + 1 < start : end - 1 > start)
5208  emsg(_("E727: Start past end"));
5209  else
5210  {
5211  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == OK)
5212  for (i = start; stride > 0 ? i <= end : i >= end; i += stride)
5213  if (list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list,
5214  (varnumber_T)i) == FAIL)
5215  break;
5216  }
5217 }

5247 #if defined(FEAT_RELTIME)
5248 /*
5249  * Convert a List to proftime_T.
5250  * Return FAIL when there is something wrong.
5251  */
5252  static int
5253 list2proftime(typval_T *arg, proftime_T *tm)
5254 {
5255  long n1, n2;
5256  int error = FALSE;
5257 
5258  if (arg->v_type != VAR_LIST || arg->vval.v_list == NULL
5259  || arg->vval.v_list->lv_len != 2)
5260  return FAIL;
5261  n1 = list_find_nr(arg->vval.v_list, 0L, &error);
5262  n2 = list_find_nr(arg->vval.v_list, 1L, &error);
5263 # ifdef MSWIN
5264  tm->HighPart = n1;
5265  tm->LowPart = n2;
5266 # else
5267  tm->tv_sec = n1;
5268  tm->tv_usec = n2;
5269 # endif
5270  return error ? FAIL : OK;
5271 }
5272 #endif /* FEAT_RELTIME */
5273 
5274 /*
5275  * "reltime()" function
5276  */
5277  static void
5278 f_reltime(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv UNUSED)
5279 {
5280 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
5281  proftime_T res;
5282  proftime_T start;
5283 
5284  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
5285  {
5286  /* No arguments: get current time. */
5287  profile_start(&res);
5288  }
5289  else if (argvars[1].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
5290  {
5291  if (list2proftime(&argvars[0], &res) == FAIL)
5292  return;
5293  profile_end(&res);
5294  }
5295  else
5296  {
5297  /* Two arguments: compute the difference. */
5298  if (list2proftime(&argvars[0], &start) == FAIL
5299  || list2proftime(&argvars[1], &res) == FAIL)
5300  return;
5301  profile_sub(&res, &start);
5302  }
5303 
5304  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == OK)
5305  {
5306  long n1, n2;
5307 
5308 # ifdef MSWIN
5309  n1 = res.HighPart;
5310  n2 = res.LowPart;
5311 # else
5312  n1 = res.tv_sec;
5313  n2 = res.tv_usec;
5314 # endif
5315  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, (varnumber_T)n1);
5316  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, (varnumber_T)n2);
5317  }
5318 #endif
5319 }

5448  v.di_tv.vval.v_string = vim_strsave(str);

5450  vim_free(v.di_tv.vval.v_string);

5456 /*

5460 f_remote_expr(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)

5499 {

5501  dictitem_T v;
5502  char_u *s = NULL;
5503 # ifdef MSWIN
5504  long_u n = 0;
5505 # endif
5506  char_u *serverid;
5507 
5508  if (check_restricted() || check_secure())
5509  {
5510  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
5511  return;
5512  }

5514  if (serverid == NULL)

5517  return; /* type error; errmsg already given */

5526  rettv->vval.v_number = (s != NULL);
5527  }
5528 # else
5529  if (check_connection() == FAIL)
5530  return;
5531 
5532  rettv->vval.v_number = serverPeekReply(X_DISPLAY,
5533  serverStrToWin(serverid), &s);
5534 # endif
5535 
5536  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN && rettv->vval.v_number > 0)
5537  {
5538  char_u *retvar;
5539 
5540  v.di_tv.v_type = VAR_STRING;
5541  v.di_tv.vval.v_string = vim_strsave(s);
5542  retvar = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[1]);
5543  if (retvar != NULL)
5544  set_var(retvar, &v.di_tv, FALSE);
5545  vim_free(v.di_tv.vval.v_string);
5546  }
5547 #else
5548  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
5549 #endif
5550 }

5559

5561  {
5562  int timeout = 0;
5563 # ifdef MSWIN

5565  long_u n = 0;
5566 # endif

5580 # endif

5583 #endif

5643 /*
5644  * "repeat()" function
5645  */
5646  static void
5647 f_repeat(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
5648 {
5649  char_u *p;
5650  int n;
5651  int slen;
5652  int len;
5653  char_u *r;
5654  int i;
5655 
5656  n = (int)tv_get_number(&argvars[1]);
5657  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_LIST)
5658  {
5659  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == OK && argvars[0].vval.v_list != NULL)
5660  while (n-- > 0)
5661  if (list_extend(rettv->vval.v_list,
5662  argvars[0].vval.v_list, NULL) == FAIL)
5663  break;
5664  }
5665  else
5666  {
5667  p = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
5668  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
5669  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
5670 
5671  slen = (int)STRLEN(p);
5672  len = slen * n;
5673  if (len <= 0)
5674  return;
5675 
5676  r = alloc(len + 1);
5677  if (r != NULL)
5678  {
5679  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
5680  mch_memmove(r + i * slen, p, (size_t)slen);
5681  r[len] = NUL;
5682  }
5683 
5684  rettv->vval.v_string = r;
5685  }
5686 }
5687 
5688 #define SP_NOMOVE 0x01 /* don't move cursor */
5689 #define SP_REPEAT 0x02 /* repeat to find outer pair */
5690 #define SP_RETCOUNT 0x04 /* return matchcount */
5691 #define SP_SETPCMARK 0x08 /* set previous context mark */
5692 #define SP_START 0x10 /* accept match at start position */
5693 #define SP_SUBPAT 0x20 /* return nr of matching sub-pattern */
5694 #define SP_END 0x40 /* leave cursor at end of match */
5695 #define SP_COLUMN 0x80 /* start at cursor column */
5696 
5697 /*
5698  * Get flags for a search function.
5699  * Possibly sets "p_ws".
5700  * Returns BACKWARD, FORWARD or zero (for an error).
5701  */
5702  static int
5703 get_search_arg(typval_T *varp, int *flagsp)
5704 {
5705  int dir = FORWARD;
5706  char_u *flags;
5707  char_u nbuf[NUMBUFLEN];
5708  int mask;
5709 
5710  if (varp->v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
5711  {
5712  flags = tv_get_string_buf_chk(varp, nbuf);
5713  if (flags == NULL)
5714  return 0; /* type error; errmsg already given */
5715  while (*flags != NUL)
5716  {
5717  switch (*flags)
5718  {
5719  case 'b': dir = BACKWARD; break;
5720  case 'w': p_ws = TRUE; break;
5721  case 'W': p_ws = FALSE; break;
5722  default: mask = 0;
5723  if (flagsp != NULL)
5724  switch (*flags)
5725  {
5726  case 'c': mask = SP_START; break;
5727  case 'e': mask = SP_END; break;
5728  case 'm': mask = SP_RETCOUNT; break;
5729  case 'n': mask = SP_NOMOVE; break;
5730  case 'p': mask = SP_SUBPAT; break;
5731  case 'r': mask = SP_REPEAT; break;
5732  case 's': mask = SP_SETPCMARK; break;
5733  case 'z': mask = SP_COLUMN; break;
5734  }
5735  if (mask == 0)
5736  {
5737  semsg(_(e_invarg2), flags);
5738  dir = 0;
5739  }
5740  else
5741  *flagsp |= mask;
5742  }
5743  if (dir == 0)
5744  break;
5745  ++flags;
5746  }
5747  }
5748  return dir;
5749 }
5750 
5751 /*
5752  * Shared by search() and searchpos() functions.
5753  */
5754  static int
5755 search_cmn(typval_T *argvars, pos_T *match_pos, int *flagsp)
5756 {
5757  int flags;
5758  char_u *pat;
5759  pos_T pos;
5760  pos_T save_cursor;
5761  int save_p_ws = p_ws;
5762  int dir;
5763  int retval = 0; /* default: FAIL */
5764  long lnum_stop = 0;
5765  proftime_T tm;
5766 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
5767  long time_limit = 0;
5768 #endif
5769  int options = SEARCH_KEEP;
5770  int subpatnum;
5771 
5772  pat = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
5773  dir = get_search_arg(&argvars[1], flagsp); /* may set p_ws */
5774  if (dir == 0)
5775  goto theend;
5776  flags = *flagsp;
5777  if (flags & SP_START)
5778  options |= SEARCH_START;
5779  if (flags & SP_END)
5780  options |= SEARCH_END;
5781  if (flags & SP_COLUMN)
5782  options |= SEARCH_COL;
5783 
5784  /* Optional arguments: line number to stop searching and timeout. */
5785  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN && argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
5786  {
5787  lnum_stop = (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], NULL);
5788  if (lnum_stop < 0)
5789  goto theend;
5790 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
5791  if (argvars[3].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
5792  {
5793  time_limit = (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[3], NULL);
5794  if (time_limit < 0)
5795  goto theend;
5796  }
5797 #endif
5798  }
5799 
5800 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
5801  /* Set the time limit, if there is one. */
5802  profile_setlimit(time_limit, &tm);
5803 #endif
5804 
5805  /*
5806  * This function does not accept SP_REPEAT and SP_RETCOUNT flags.
5807  * Check to make sure only those flags are set.
5808  * Also, Only the SP_NOMOVE or the SP_SETPCMARK flag can be set. Both
5809  * flags cannot be set. Check for that condition also.
5810  */
5811  if (((flags & (SP_REPEAT | SP_RETCOUNT)) != 0)
5812  || ((flags & SP_NOMOVE) && (flags & SP_SETPCMARK)))
5813  {
5814  semsg(_(e_invarg2), tv_get_string(&argvars[1]));
5815  goto theend;
5816  }
5817 
5818  pos = save_cursor = curwin->w_cursor;
5819  subpatnum = searchit(curwin, curbuf, &pos, NULL, dir, pat, 1L,
5820  options, RE_SEARCH, (linenr_T)lnum_stop, &tm, NULL);
5821  if (subpatnum != FAIL)
5822  {
5823  if (flags & SP_SUBPAT)
5824  retval = subpatnum;
5825  else
5826  retval = pos.lnum;
5827  if (flags & SP_SETPCMARK)
5828  setpcmark();
5829  curwin->w_cursor = pos;
5830  if (match_pos != NULL)
5831  {
5832  /* Store the match cursor position */
5833  match_pos->lnum = pos.lnum;
5834  match_pos->col = pos.col + 1;
5835  }
5836  /* "/$" will put the cursor after the end of the line, may need to
5837  * correct that here */
5838  check_cursor();
5839  }
5840 
5841  /* If 'n' flag is used: restore cursor position. */
5842  if (flags & SP_NOMOVE)
5843  curwin->w_cursor = save_cursor;
5844  else
5845  curwin->w_set_curswant = TRUE;
5846 theend:
5847  p_ws = save_p_ws;
5848 
5849  return retval;
5850 }

5857  float_T
5858 vim_round(float_T f)

5860  return f > 0 ? floor(f + 0.5) : ceil(f - 0.5);
5861 }
