6066 /*
6067  * Used by searchpair() and searchpairpos()
6068  */
6069  static int
6070 searchpair_cmn(typval_T *argvars, pos_T *match_pos)
6071 {
6072  char_u *spat, *mpat, *epat;
6073  typval_T *skip;
6074  int save_p_ws = p_ws;
6075  int dir;
6076  int flags = 0;
6077  char_u nbuf1[NUMBUFLEN];
6078  char_u nbuf2[NUMBUFLEN];
6079  int retval = 0; /* default: FAIL */
6080  long lnum_stop = 0;
6081  long time_limit = 0;
6082 
6083  /* Get the three pattern arguments: start, middle, end. Will result in an
6084  * error if not a valid argument. */
6085  spat = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
6086  mpat = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[1], nbuf1);
6087  epat = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[2], nbuf2);
6088  if (spat == NULL || mpat == NULL || epat == NULL)
6089  goto theend; /* type error */
6090 
6091  /* Handle the optional fourth argument: flags */
6092  dir = get_search_arg(&argvars[3], &flags); /* may set p_ws */
6093  if (dir == 0)
6094  goto theend;
6095 
6096  /* Don't accept SP_END or SP_SUBPAT.
6097  * Only one of the SP_NOMOVE or SP_SETPCMARK flags can be set.
6098  */
6099  if ((flags & (SP_END | SP_SUBPAT)) != 0
6100  || ((flags & SP_NOMOVE) && (flags & SP_SETPCMARK)))
6101  {
6102  semsg(_(e_invarg2), tv_get_string(&argvars[3]));
6103  goto theend;
6104  }
6105 
6106  /* Using 'r' implies 'W', otherwise it doesn't work. */
6107  if (flags & SP_REPEAT)
6108  p_ws = FALSE;
6109 
6110  /* Optional fifth argument: skip expression */
6111  if (argvars[3].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN
6112  || argvars[4].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
6113  skip = NULL;
6114  else
6115  {
6116  skip = &argvars[4];
6117  if (skip->v_type != VAR_FUNC && skip->v_type != VAR_PARTIAL
6118  && skip->v_type != VAR_STRING)
6119  {
6120  /* Type error */
6121  semsg(_(e_invarg2), tv_get_string(&argvars[4]));
6122  goto theend;
6123  }
6124  if (argvars[5].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
6125  {
6126  lnum_stop = (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[5], NULL);
6127  if (lnum_stop < 0)
6128  {
6129  semsg(_(e_invarg2), tv_get_string(&argvars[5]));
6130  goto theend;
6131  }
6132 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
6133  if (argvars[6].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
6134  {
6135  time_limit = (long)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[6], NULL);
6136  if (time_limit < 0)
6137  {
6138  semsg(_(e_invarg2), tv_get_string(&argvars[6]));
6139  goto theend;
6140  }
6141  }
6142 #endif
6143  }
6144  }
6145 
6146  retval = do_searchpair(spat, mpat, epat, dir, skip, flags,
6147  match_pos, lnum_stop, time_limit);
6148 
6149 theend:
6150  p_ws = save_p_ws;
6151 
6152  return retval;
6153 }

6164 /*
6165  * "searchpairpos()" function
6166  */
6167  static void
6168 f_searchpairpos(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
6169 {
6170  pos_T match_pos;
6171  int lnum = 0;
6172  int col = 0;
6173 
6174  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == FAIL)
6175  return;
6176 
6177  if (searchpair_cmn(argvars, &match_pos) > 0)
6178  {
6179  lnum = match_pos.lnum;
6180  col = match_pos.col;
6181  }
6182 
6183  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, (varnumber_T)lnum);
6184  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, (varnumber_T)col);
6185 }
6186 
6187 /*
6188  * Search for a start/middle/end thing.
6189  * Used by searchpair(), see its documentation for the details.
6190  * Returns 0 or -1 for no match,
6191  */
6192  long
6193 do_searchpair(
6194  char_u *spat, /* start pattern */
6195  char_u *mpat, /* middle pattern */
6196  char_u *epat, /* end pattern */
6197  int dir, /* BACKWARD or FORWARD */
6198  typval_T *skip, /* skip expression */
6199  int flags, /* SP_SETPCMARK and other SP_ values */
6200  pos_T *match_pos,
6201  linenr_T lnum_stop, /* stop at this line if not zero */
6202  long time_limit UNUSED) /* stop after this many msec */
6203 {
6204  char_u *save_cpo;
6205  char_u *pat, *pat2 = NULL, *pat3 = NULL;
6206  long retval = 0;
6207  pos_T pos;
6208  pos_T firstpos;
6209  pos_T foundpos;
6210  pos_T save_cursor;
6211  pos_T save_pos;
6212  int n;
6213  int r;
6214  int nest = 1;
6215  int use_skip = FALSE;
6216  int err;
6217  int options = SEARCH_KEEP;
6218  proftime_T tm;
6219 
6220  /* Make 'cpoptions' empty, the 'l' flag should not be used here. */
6221  save_cpo = p_cpo;
6222  p_cpo = empty_option;
6223 
6224 #ifdef FEAT_RELTIME
6225  /* Set the time limit, if there is one. */
6226  profile_setlimit(time_limit, &tm);
6227 #endif
6228 
6229  /* Make two search patterns: start/end (pat2, for in nested pairs) and
6230  * start/middle/end (pat3, for the top pair). */
6231  pat2 = alloc(STRLEN(spat) + STRLEN(epat) + 17);
6232  pat3 = alloc(STRLEN(spat) + STRLEN(mpat) + STRLEN(epat) + 25);
6233  if (pat2 == NULL || pat3 == NULL)
6234  goto theend;
6235  sprintf((char *)pat2, "\\m\\(%s\\m\\)\\|\\(%s\\m\\)", spat, epat);
6236  if (*mpat == NUL)
6237  STRCPY(pat3, pat2);
6238  else
6239  sprintf((char *)pat3, "\\m\\(%s\\m\\)\\|\\(%s\\m\\)\\|\\(%s\\m\\)",
6240  spat, epat, mpat);
6241  if (flags & SP_START)
6242  options |= SEARCH_START;
6243 
6244  if (skip != NULL)
6245  {
6246  /* Empty string means to not use the skip expression. */
6247  if (skip->v_type == VAR_STRING || skip->v_type == VAR_FUNC)
6248  use_skip = skip->vval.v_string != NULL
6249  && *skip->vval.v_string != NUL;
6250  }
6251 
6252  save_cursor = curwin->w_cursor;
6253  pos = curwin->w_cursor;
6254  CLEAR_POS(&firstpos);
6255  CLEAR_POS(&foundpos);
6256  pat = pat3;
6257  for (;;)
6258  {
6259  n = searchit(curwin, curbuf, &pos, NULL, dir, pat, 1L,
6260  options, RE_SEARCH, lnum_stop, &tm, NULL);
6261  if (n == FAIL || (firstpos.lnum != 0 && EQUAL_POS(pos, firstpos)))
6262  /* didn't find it or found the first match again: FAIL */
6263  break;
6264 
6265  if (firstpos.lnum == 0)
6266  firstpos = pos;
6267  if (EQUAL_POS(pos, foundpos))
6268  {
6269  /* Found the same position again. Can happen with a pattern that
6270  * has "\zs" at the end and searching backwards. Advance one
6271  * character and try again. */
6272  if (dir == BACKWARD)
6273  decl(&pos);
6274  else
6275  incl(&pos);
6276  }
6277  foundpos = pos;
6278 
6279  /* clear the start flag to avoid getting stuck here */
6280  options &= ~SEARCH_START;
6281 
6282  /* If the skip pattern matches, ignore this match. */
6283  if (use_skip)
6284  {
6285  save_pos = curwin->w_cursor;
6286  curwin->w_cursor = pos;
6287  err = FALSE;
6288  r = eval_expr_to_bool(skip, &err);
6289  curwin->w_cursor = save_pos;
6290  if (err)
6291  {
6292  /* Evaluating {skip} caused an error, break here. */
6293  curwin->w_cursor = save_cursor;
6294  retval = -1;
6295  break;
6296  }
6297  if (r)
6298  continue;
6299  }
6300 
6301  if ((dir == BACKWARD && n == 3) || (dir == FORWARD && n == 2))
6302  {
6303  /* Found end when searching backwards or start when searching
6304  * forward: nested pair. */
6305  ++nest;
6306  pat = pat2; /* nested, don't search for middle */
6307  }
6308  else
6309  {
6310  /* Found end when searching forward or start when searching
6311  * backward: end of (nested) pair; or found middle in outer pair. */
6312  if (--nest == 1)
6313  pat = pat3; /* outer level, search for middle */
6314  }
6315 
6316  if (nest == 0)
6317  {
6318  /* Found the match: return matchcount or line number. */
6319  if (flags & SP_RETCOUNT)
6320  ++retval;
6321  else
6322  retval = pos.lnum;
6323  if (flags & SP_SETPCMARK)
6324  setpcmark();
6325  curwin->w_cursor = pos;
6326  if (!(flags & SP_REPEAT))
6327  break;
6328  nest = 1; /* search for next unmatched */
6329  }
6330  }
6331 
6332  if (match_pos != NULL)
6333  {
6334  /* Store the match cursor position */
6335  match_pos->lnum = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
6336  match_pos->col = curwin->w_cursor.col + 1;
6337  }
6338 
6339  /* If 'n' flag is used or search failed: restore cursor position. */
6340  if ((flags & SP_NOMOVE) || retval == 0)
6341  curwin->w_cursor = save_cursor;
6342 
6343 theend:
6344  vim_free(pat2);
6345  vim_free(pat3);
6346  if (p_cpo == empty_option)
6347  p_cpo = save_cpo;
6348  else
6349  /* Darn, evaluating the {skip} expression changed the value. */
6350  free_string_option(save_cpo);
6351 
6352  return retval;
6353 }

6356  * "searchpos()" function
6357  */
6358  static void
6359 f_searchpos(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
6360 {
6361  pos_T match_pos;
6362  int lnum = 0;
6363  int col = 0;
6364  int n;
6365  int flags = 0;
6366 
6367  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == FAIL)
6368  return;
6369 
6370  n = search_cmn(argvars, &match_pos, &flags);
6371  if (n > 0)
6372  {
6373  lnum = match_pos.lnum;
6374  col = match_pos.col;
6375  }
6376 
6377  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, (varnumber_T)lnum);
6378  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, (varnumber_T)col);
6379  if (flags & SP_SUBPAT)
6380  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, (varnumber_T)n);
6381 }

6527  static void
6528 f_setpos(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
6529 {

6555  else if (name[0] == '\'' && name[1] != NUL && name[2] == NUL)
6556  {
6557  /* set mark */
6558  if (setmark_pos(name[1], &pos, fnum) == OK)
6559  rettv->vval.v_number = 0;

6563  }

6567 /*
6568  * "setreg()" function
6569  */
6570  static void
6571 f_setreg(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
6572 {
6573  int regname;
6574  char_u *strregname;
6575  char_u *stropt;
6576  char_u *strval;
6577  int append;
6578  char_u yank_type;
6579  long block_len;
6580 
6581  block_len = -1;
6582  yank_type = MAUTO;
6583  append = FALSE;
6584 
6585  strregname = tv_get_string_chk(argvars);
6586  rettv->vval.v_number = 1; /* FAIL is default */
6587 
6588  if (strregname == NULL)
6589  return; /* type error; errmsg already given */
6590  regname = *strregname;
6591  if (regname == 0 || regname == '@')
6592  regname = '"';
6593 
6594  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
6595  {
6596  stropt = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[2]);
6597  if (stropt == NULL)
6598  return; /* type error */
6599  for (; *stropt != NUL; ++stropt)
6600  switch (*stropt)
6601  {
6602  case 'a': case 'A': /* append */
6603  append = TRUE;
6604  break;
6605  case 'v': case 'c': /* character-wise selection */
6606  yank_type = MCHAR;
6607  break;
6608  case 'V': case 'l': /* line-wise selection */
6609  yank_type = MLINE;
6610  break;
6611  case 'b': case Ctrl_V: /* block-wise selection */
6612  yank_type = MBLOCK;
6613  if (VIM_ISDIGIT(stropt[1]))
6614  {
6615  ++stropt;
6616  block_len = getdigits(&stropt) - 1;
6617  --stropt;
6618  }
6619  break;
6620  }
6621  }
6622 
6623  if (argvars[1].v_type == VAR_LIST)
6624  {
6625  char_u **lstval;
6626  char_u **allocval;
6627  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN];
6628  char_u **curval;
6629  char_u **curallocval;
6630  list_T *ll = argvars[1].vval.v_list;
6631  listitem_T *li;
6632  int len;
6633 
6634  /* If the list is NULL handle like an empty list. */
6635  len = ll == NULL ? 0 : ll->lv_len;
6636 
6637  /* First half: use for pointers to result lines; second half: use for
6638  * pointers to allocated copies. */
6639  lstval = ALLOC_MULT(char_u *, (len + 1) * 2);
6640  if (lstval == NULL)
6641  return;
6642  curval = lstval;
6643  allocval = lstval + len + 2;
6644  curallocval = allocval;
6645 
6646  for (li = ll == NULL ? NULL : ll->lv_first; li != NULL;
6647  li = li->li_next)
6648  {
6649  strval = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&li->li_tv, buf);
6650  if (strval == NULL)
6651  goto free_lstval;
6652  if (strval == buf)
6653  {
6654  /* Need to make a copy, next tv_get_string_buf_chk() will
6655  * overwrite the string. */
6656  strval = vim_strsave(buf);
6657  if (strval == NULL)
6658  goto free_lstval;
6659  *curallocval++ = strval;
6660  }
6661  *curval++ = strval;
6662  }
6663  *curval++ = NULL;
6664 
6665  write_reg_contents_lst(regname, lstval, -1,
6666  append, yank_type, block_len);
6667 free_lstval:
6668  while (curallocval > allocval)
6669  vim_free(*--curallocval);
6670  vim_free(lstval);
6671  }
6672  else
6673  {
6674  strval = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[1]);
6675  if (strval == NULL)
6676  return;
6677  write_reg_contents_ex(regname, strval, -1,
6678  append, yank_type, block_len);
6679  }
6680  rettv->vval.v_number = 0;
6681 }

6683 /*
6684  * "settagstack()" function
6685  */
6686  static void
6687 f_settagstack(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
6688 {
6689  static char *e_invact2 = N_("E962: Invalid action: '%s'");
6690  win_T *wp;
6691  dict_T *d;
6692  int action = 'r';
6693 
6694  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
6695 
6696  // first argument: window number or id
6697  wp = find_win_by_nr_or_id(&argvars[0]);
6698  if (wp == NULL)
6699  return;
6700 
6701  // second argument: dict with items to set in the tag stack
6702  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_DICT)
6703  {
6704  emsg(_(e_dictreq));
6705  return;
6706  }
6707  d = argvars[1].vval.v_dict;
6708  if (d == NULL)
6709  return;
6710 
6711  // third argument: action - 'a' for append and 'r' for replace.
6712  // default is to replace the stack.
6713  if (argvars[2].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
6714  action = 'r';
6715  else if (argvars[2].v_type == VAR_STRING)
6716  {
6717  char_u *actstr;
6718  actstr = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[2]);
6719  if (actstr == NULL)
6720  return;
6721  if ((*actstr == 'r' || *actstr == 'a') && actstr[1] == NUL)
6722  action = *actstr;
6723  else
6724  {
6725  semsg(_(e_invact2), actstr);
6726  return;
6727  }
6728  }
6729  else
6730  {
6731  emsg(_(e_stringreq));
6732  return;
6733  }
6734 
6735  if (set_tagstack(wp, d, action) == OK)
6736  rettv->vval.v_number = 0;
6737 }

6768 /*
6769  * shiftwidth() function
6770  */
6771  static void
6772 f_shiftwidth(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
6773 {
6774  rettv->vval.v_number = 0;
6775 
6776  if (argvars[0].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
6777  {
6778  long col;
6779 
6780  col = (long)tv_get_number_chk(argvars, NULL);
6781  if (col < 0)
6782  return; // type error; errmsg already given
6783 #ifdef FEAT_VARTABS
6784  rettv->vval.v_number = get_sw_value_col(curbuf, col);
6785  return;
6786 #endif
6787  }
6788 
6789  rettv->vval.v_number = get_sw_value(curbuf);
6790 }

6841 /*
6842  * "spellbadword()" function
6843  */
6844  static void
6845 f_spellbadword(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
6846 {
6847  char_u *word = (char_u *)"";
6848  hlf_T attr = HLF_COUNT;
6849  int len = 0;
6850 
6851  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == FAIL)
6852  return;
6853 
6854 #ifdef FEAT_SPELL
6855  if (argvars[0].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
6856  {
6857  /* Find the start and length of the badly spelled word. */
6858  len = spell_move_to(curwin, FORWARD, TRUE, TRUE, &attr);
6859  if (len != 0)
6860  {
6861  word = ml_get_cursor();
6862  curwin->w_set_curswant = TRUE;
6863  }
6864  }
6865  else if (curwin->w_p_spell && *curbuf->b_s.b_p_spl != NUL)
6866  {
6867  char_u *str = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
6868  int capcol = -1;
6869 
6870  if (str != NULL)
6871  {
6872  /* Check the argument for spelling. */
6873  while (*str != NUL)
6874  {
6875  len = spell_check(curwin, str, &attr, &capcol, FALSE);
6876  if (attr != HLF_COUNT)
6877  {
6878  word = str;
6879  break;
6880  }
6881  str += len;
6882  capcol -= len;
6883  len = 0;
6884  }
6885  }
6886  }
6887 #endif
6888 
6889  list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list, word, len);
6890  list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list, (char_u *)(
6891  attr == HLF_SPB ? "bad" :
6892  attr == HLF_SPR ? "rare" :
6893  attr == HLF_SPL ? "local" :
6894  attr == HLF_SPC ? "caps" :
6895  ""), -1);
6896 }

6898 /*
6899  * "spellsuggest()" function
6900  */
6901  static void
6902 f_spellsuggest(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
6903 {
6904 #ifdef FEAT_SPELL
6905  char_u *str;
6906  int typeerr = FALSE;
6907  int maxcount;
6908  garray_T ga;
6909  int i;
6910  listitem_T *li;
6911  int need_capital = FALSE;
6912 #endif
6913 
6914  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == FAIL)
6915  return;
6916 
6917 #ifdef FEAT_SPELL
6918  if (curwin->w_p_spell && *curwin->w_s->b_p_spl != NUL)
6919  {
6920  str = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
6921  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
6922  {
6923  maxcount = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &typeerr);
6924  if (maxcount <= 0)
6925  return;
6926  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
6927  {
6928  need_capital = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &typeerr);
6929  if (typeerr)
6930  return;
6931  }
6932  }
6933  else
6934  maxcount = 25;
6935 
6936  spell_suggest_list(&ga, str, maxcount, need_capital, FALSE);
6937 
6938  for (i = 0; i < ga.ga_len; ++i)
6939  {
6940  str = ((char_u **)ga.ga_data)[i];
6941 
6942  li = listitem_alloc();
6943  if (li == NULL)
6944  vim_free(str);
6945  else
6946  {
6947  li->li_tv.v_type = VAR_STRING;
6948  li->li_tv.v_lock = 0;
6949  li->li_tv.vval.v_string = str;
6950  list_append(rettv->vval.v_list, li);
6951  }
6952  }
6953  ga_clear(&ga);
6954  }
6955 #endif
6956 }

6958  static void
6959 f_split(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
6960 {
6961  char_u *str;
6962  char_u *end;
6963  char_u *pat = NULL;
6964  regmatch_T regmatch;
6965  char_u patbuf[NUMBUFLEN];
6966  char_u *save_cpo;
6967  int match;
6968  colnr_T col = 0;
6969  int keepempty = FALSE;
6970  int typeerr = FALSE;
6971 
6972  /* Make 'cpoptions' empty, the 'l' flag should not be used here. */
6973  save_cpo = p_cpo;
6974  p_cpo = (char_u *)"";
6975 
6976  str = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
6977  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
6978  {
6979  pat = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[1], patbuf);
6980  if (pat == NULL)
6981  typeerr = TRUE;
6982  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
6983  keepempty = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &typeerr);
6984  }
6985  if (pat == NULL || *pat == NUL)
6986  pat = (char_u *)"[\\x01- ]\\+";
6987 
6988  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == FAIL)
6989  return;
6990  if (typeerr)
6991  return;
6992 
6993  regmatch.regprog = vim_regcomp(pat, RE_MAGIC + RE_STRING);
6994  if (regmatch.regprog != NULL)
6995  {
6996  regmatch.rm_ic = FALSE;
6997  while (*str != NUL || keepempty)
6998  {
6999  if (*str == NUL)
7000  match = FALSE; /* empty item at the end */
7001  else
7002  match = vim_regexec_nl(&regmatch, str, col);
7003  if (match)
7004  end = regmatch.startp[0];
7005  else
7006  end = str + STRLEN(str);
7007  if (keepempty || end > str || (rettv->vval.v_list->lv_len > 0
7008  && *str != NUL && match && end < regmatch.endp[0]))
7009  {
7010  if (list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list, str,
7011  (int)(end - str)) == FAIL)
7012  break;
7013  }
7014  if (!match)
7015  break;
7016  // Advance to just after the match.
7017  if (regmatch.endp[0] > str)
7018  col = 0;
7019  else
7020  // Don't get stuck at the same match.
7021  col = (*mb_ptr2len)(regmatch.endp[0]);
7022  str = regmatch.endp[0];
7023  }
7024 
7025  vim_regfree(regmatch.regprog);
7026  }
7027 
7028  p_cpo = save_cpo;
7029 }

7047 /*
7048  * "str2float()" function
7049  */
7050  static void
7051 f_str2float(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7052 {
7053  char_u *p = skipwhite(tv_get_string(&argvars[0]));
7054  int isneg = (*p == '-');
7055 
7056  if (*p == '+' || *p == '-')
7057  p = skipwhite(p + 1);
7058  (void)string2float(p, &rettv->vval.v_float);
7059  if (isneg)
7060  rettv->vval.v_float *= -1;
7061  rettv->v_type = VAR_FLOAT;
7062 }

7065 /*
7066  * "str2list()" function
7067  */
7068  static void
7069 f_str2list(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7070 {
7071  char_u *p;
7072  int utf8 = FALSE;
7073 
7074  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) == FAIL)
7075  return;
7076 
7077  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
7078  utf8 = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], NULL);
7079 
7080  p = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
7081 
7082  if (has_mbyte || utf8)
7083  {
7084  int (*ptr2len)(char_u *);
7085  int (*ptr2char)(char_u *);
7086 
7087  if (utf8 || enc_utf8)
7088  {
7089  ptr2len = utf_ptr2len;
7090  ptr2char = utf_ptr2char;
7091  }
7092  else
7093  {
7094  ptr2len = mb_ptr2len;
7095  ptr2char = mb_ptr2char;
7096  }
7097 
7098  for ( ; *p != NUL; p += (*ptr2len)(p))
7099  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, (*ptr2char)(p));
7100  }
7101  else
7102  for ( ; *p != NUL; ++p)
7103  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, *p);
7104 }

7106 /*
7107  * "str2nr()" function
7108  */
7109  static void
7110 f_str2nr(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7111 {
7112  int base = 10;
7113  char_u *p;
7114  varnumber_T n;
7115  int what = 0;
7116  int isneg;
7117 
7118  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
7119  {
7120  base = (int)tv_get_number(&argvars[1]);
7121  if (base != 2 && base != 8 && base != 10 && base != 16)
7122  {
7123  emsg(_(e_invarg));
7124  return;
7125  }
7126  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN && tv_get_number(&argvars[2]))
7127  what |= STR2NR_QUOTE;
7128  }
7129 
7130  p = skipwhite(tv_get_string(&argvars[0]));
7131  isneg = (*p == '-');
7132  if (*p == '+' || *p == '-')
7133  p = skipwhite(p + 1);
7134  switch (base)
7135  {
7136  case 2: what |= STR2NR_BIN + STR2NR_FORCE; break;
7137  case 8: what |= STR2NR_OCT + STR2NR_FORCE; break;
7138  case 16: what |= STR2NR_HEX + STR2NR_FORCE; break;
7139  }
7140  vim_str2nr(p, NULL, NULL, what, &n, NULL, 0, FALSE);
7141  // Text after the number is silently ignored.
7142  if (isneg)
7143  rettv->vval.v_number = -n;
7144  else
7145  rettv->vval.v_number = n;
7146 
7147 }

7149 #ifdef HAVE_STRFTIME
7150 /*
7151  * "strftime({format}[, {time}])" function
7152  */
7153  static void
7154 f_strftime(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7155 {
7156  char_u result_buf[256];
7157  struct tm tmval;
7158  struct tm *curtime;
7159  time_t seconds;
7160  char_u *p;
7161 
7162  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
7163 
7164  p = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
7165  if (argvars[1].v_type == VAR_UNKNOWN)
7166  seconds = time(NULL);
7167  else
7168  seconds = (time_t)tv_get_number(&argvars[1]);
7169  curtime = vim_localtime(&seconds, &tmval);
7170  /* MSVC returns NULL for an invalid value of seconds. */
7171  if (curtime == NULL)
7172  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strsave((char_u *)_("(Invalid)"));
7173  else
7174  {
7175  vimconv_T conv;
7176  char_u *enc;
7177 
7178  conv.vc_type = CONV_NONE;
7179  enc = enc_locale();
7180  convert_setup(&conv, p_enc, enc);
7181  if (conv.vc_type != CONV_NONE)
7182  p = string_convert(&conv, p, NULL);
7183  if (p != NULL)
7184  (void)strftime((char *)result_buf, sizeof(result_buf),
7185  (char *)p, curtime);
7186  else
7187  result_buf[0] = NUL;
7188 
7189  if (conv.vc_type != CONV_NONE)
7190  vim_free(p);
7191  convert_setup(&conv, enc, p_enc);
7192  if (conv.vc_type != CONV_NONE)
7193  rettv->vval.v_string = string_convert(&conv, result_buf, NULL);
7194  else
7195  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strsave(result_buf);
7196 
7197  /* Release conversion descriptors */
7198  convert_setup(&conv, NULL, NULL);
7199  vim_free(enc);
7200  }
7201 }
7202 #endif

7204 /*
7205  * "strgetchar()" function
7206  */
7207  static void
7208 f_strgetchar(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7209 {
7210  char_u *str;
7211  int len;
7212  int error = FALSE;
7213  int charidx;
7214  int byteidx = 0;
7215 
7216  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
7217  str = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[0]);
7218  if (str == NULL)
7219  return;
7220  len = (int)STRLEN(str);
7221  charidx = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error);
7222  if (error)
7223  return;
7224 
7225  while (charidx >= 0 && byteidx < len)
7226  {
7227  if (charidx == 0)
7228  {
7229  rettv->vval.v_number = mb_ptr2char(str + byteidx);
7230  break;
7231  }
7232  --charidx;
7233  byteidx += MB_CPTR2LEN(str + byteidx);
7234  }
7235 }

7237 /*
7238  * "stridx()" function
7239  */
7240  static void
7241 f_stridx(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7242 {
7243  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN];
7244  char_u *needle;
7245  char_u *haystack;
7246  char_u *save_haystack;
7247  char_u *pos;
7248  int start_idx;
7249 
7250  needle = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[1]);
7251  save_haystack = haystack = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[0], buf);
7252  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
7253  if (needle == NULL || haystack == NULL)
7254  return; /* type error; errmsg already given */
7255 
7256  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
7257  {
7258  int error = FALSE;
7259 
7260  start_idx = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], &error);
7261  if (error || start_idx >= (int)STRLEN(haystack))
7262  return;
7263  if (start_idx >= 0)
7264  haystack += start_idx;
7265  }
7266 
7267  pos = (char_u *)strstr((char *)haystack, (char *)needle);
7268  if (pos != NULL)
7269  rettv->vval.v_number = (varnumber_T)(pos - save_haystack);
7270 }

7352 /*
7353  * "strcharpart()" function
7354  */
7355  static void
7356 f_strcharpart(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7357 {
7358  char_u *p;
7359  int nchar;
7360  int nbyte = 0;
7361  int charlen;
7362  int len = 0;
7363  int slen;
7364  int error = FALSE;
7365 
7366  p = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
7367  slen = (int)STRLEN(p);
7368 
7369  nchar = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error);
7370  if (!error)
7371  {
7372  if (nchar > 0)
7373  while (nchar > 0 && nbyte < slen)
7374  {
7375  nbyte += MB_CPTR2LEN(p + nbyte);
7376  --nchar;
7377  }
7378  else
7379  nbyte = nchar;
7380  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
7381  {
7382  charlen = (int)tv_get_number(&argvars[2]);
7383  while (charlen > 0 && nbyte + len < slen)
7384  {
7385  int off = nbyte + len;
7386 
7387  if (off < 0)
7388  len += 1;
7389  else
7390  len += MB_CPTR2LEN(p + off);
7391  --charlen;
7392  }
7393  }
7394  else
7395  len = slen - nbyte; /* default: all bytes that are available. */
7396  }
7397 
7398  /*
7399  * Only return the overlap between the specified part and the actual
7400  * string.
7401  */
7402  if (nbyte < 0)
7403  {
7404  len += nbyte;
7405  nbyte = 0;
7406  }
7407  else if (nbyte > slen)
7408  nbyte = slen;
7409  if (len < 0)
7410  len = 0;
7411  else if (nbyte + len > slen)
7412  len = slen - nbyte;
7413 
7414  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
7415  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strnsave(p + nbyte, len);
7416 }
7417 
7418 /*
7419  * "strpart()" function
7420  */
7421  static void
7422 f_strpart(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7423 {
7424  char_u *p;
7425  int n;
7426  int len;
7427  int slen;
7428  int error = FALSE;
7429 
7430  p = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
7431  slen = (int)STRLEN(p);
7432 
7433  n = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error);
7434  if (error)
7435  len = 0;
7436  else if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
7437  len = (int)tv_get_number(&argvars[2]);
7438  else
7439  len = slen - n; /* default len: all bytes that are available. */
7440 
7441  /*
7442  * Only return the overlap between the specified part and the actual
7443  * string.
7444  */
7445  if (n < 0)
7446  {
7447  len += n;
7448  n = 0;
7449  }
7450  else if (n > slen)
7451  n = slen;
7452  if (len < 0)
7453  len = 0;
7454  else if (n + len > slen)
7455  len = slen - n;
7456 
7457  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
7458  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strnsave(p + n, len);
7459 }

7461 /*
7462  * "strridx()" function
7463  */
7464  static void
7465 f_strridx(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7466 {
7467  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN];
7468  char_u *needle;
7469  char_u *haystack;
7470  char_u *rest;
7471  char_u *lastmatch = NULL;
7472  int haystack_len, end_idx;
7473 
7474  needle = tv_get_string_chk(&argvars[1]);
7475  haystack = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[0], buf);
7476 
7477  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
7478  if (needle == NULL || haystack == NULL)
7479  return; /* type error; errmsg already given */
7480 
7481  haystack_len = (int)STRLEN(haystack);
7482  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
7483  {
7484  /* Third argument: upper limit for index */
7485  end_idx = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[2], NULL);
7486  if (end_idx < 0)
7487  return; /* can never find a match */
7488  }
7489  else
7490  end_idx = haystack_len;
7491 
7492  if (*needle == NUL)
7493  {
7494  /* Empty string matches past the end. */
7495  lastmatch = haystack + end_idx;
7496  }
7497  else
7498  {
7499  for (rest = haystack; *rest != '\0'; ++rest)
7500  {
7501  rest = (char_u *)strstr((char *)rest, (char *)needle);
7502  if (rest == NULL || rest > haystack + end_idx)
7503  break;
7504  lastmatch = rest;
7505  }
7506  }
7507 
7508  if (lastmatch == NULL)
7509  rettv->vval.v_number = -1;
7510  else
7511  rettv->vval.v_number = (varnumber_T)(lastmatch - haystack);
7512 }

7518 f_strtrans(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)

7522 }

7524 /*
7525  * "submatch()" function
7526  */
7527  static void
7528 f_submatch(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7529 {
7530  int error = FALSE;
7531  int no;
7532  int retList = 0;
7533 
7534  no = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[0], &error);
7535  if (error)
7536  return;
7537  if (no < 0 || no >= NSUBEXP)
7538  {
7539  semsg(_("E935: invalid submatch number: %d"), no);
7540  return;
7541  }
7542  if (argvars[1].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
7543  retList = (int)tv_get_number_chk(&argvars[1], &error);
7544  if (error)
7545  return;
7546 
7547  if (retList == 0)
7548  {
7549  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
7550  rettv->vval.v_string = reg_submatch(no);
7551  }
7552  else
7553  {
7554  rettv->v_type = VAR_LIST;
7555  rettv->vval.v_list = reg_submatch_list(no);
7556  }
7557 }

7640 /*
7641  * "synIDattr(id, what [, mode])" function
7642  */
7643  static void
7644 f_synIDattr(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
7645 {
7646  char_u *p = NULL;
7647 #ifdef FEAT_SYN_HL
7648  int id;
7649  char_u *what;
7650  char_u *mode;
7651  char_u modebuf[NUMBUFLEN];
7652  int modec;
7653 
7654  id = (int)tv_get_number(&argvars[0]);
7655  what = tv_get_string(&argvars[1]);
7656  if (argvars[2].v_type != VAR_UNKNOWN)
7657  {
7658  mode = tv_get_string_buf(&argvars[2], modebuf);
7659  modec = TOLOWER_ASC(mode[0]);
7660  if (modec != 't' && modec != 'c' && modec != 'g')
7661  modec = 0; /* replace invalid with current */
7662  }
7663  else
7664  {
7665 #if defined(FEAT_GUI) || defined(FEAT_TERMGUICOLORS)
7666  if (USE_24BIT)
7667  modec = 'g';
7668  else
7669 #endif
7670  if (t_colors > 1)
7671  modec = 'c';
7672  else
7673  modec = 't';
7674  }
7675 
7676  switch (TOLOWER_ASC(what[0]))
7677  {
7678  case 'b':
7679  if (TOLOWER_ASC(what[1]) == 'g') /* bg[#] */
7680  p = highlight_color(id, what, modec);
7681  else /* bold */
7682  p = highlight_has_attr(id, HL_BOLD, modec);
7683  break;
7684 
7685  case 'f': /* fg[#] or font */
7686  p = highlight_color(id, what, modec);
7687  break;
7688 
7689  case 'i':
7690  if (TOLOWER_ASC(what[1]) == 'n') /* inverse */
7691  p = highlight_has_attr(id, HL_INVERSE, modec);
7692  else /* italic */
7693  p = highlight_has_attr(id, HL_ITALIC, modec);
7694  break;
7695 
7696  case 'n': /* name */
7697  p = get_highlight_name_ext(NULL, id - 1, FALSE);
7698  break;
7699 
7700  case 'r': /* reverse */
7701  p = highlight_has_attr(id, HL_INVERSE, modec);
7702  break;
7703 
7704  case 's':
7705  if (TOLOWER_ASC(what[1]) == 'p') /* sp[#] */
7706  p = highlight_color(id, what, modec);
7707  /* strikeout */
7708  else if (TOLOWER_ASC(what[1]) == 't' &&
7709  TOLOWER_ASC(what[2]) == 'r')
7710  p = highlight_has_attr(id, HL_STRIKETHROUGH, modec);
7711  else /* standout */
7712  p = highlight_has_attr(id, HL_STANDOUT, modec);
7713  break;
7714 
7715  case 'u':
7716  if (STRLEN(what) <= 5 || TOLOWER_ASC(what[5]) != 'c')
7717  /* underline */
7718  p = highlight_has_attr(id, HL_UNDERLINE, modec);
7719  else
7720  /* undercurl */
7721  p = highlight_has_attr(id, HL_UNDERCURL, modec);
7722  break;
7723  }
7724 
7725  if (p != NULL)
7726  p = vim_strsave(p);
7727 #endif
7728  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
7729  rettv->vval.v_string = p;
7730 }

7753  * "synconcealed(lnum, col)" function
7754  */
7755  static void
7756 f_synconcealed(typval_T *argvars UNUSED, typval_T *rettv)
7757 {
7758 #if defined(FEAT_SYN_HL) && defined(FEAT_CONCEAL)
7759  linenr_T lnum;
7760  colnr_T col;
7761  int syntax_flags = 0;
7762  int cchar;
7763  int matchid = 0;
7764  char_u str[NUMBUFLEN];
7765 #endif
7766 
7767  rettv_list_set(rettv, NULL);
7768 
7769 #if defined(FEAT_SYN_HL) && defined(FEAT_CONCEAL)
7770  lnum = tv_get_lnum(argvars); /* -1 on type error */
7771  col = (colnr_T)tv_get_number(&argvars[1]) - 1; /* -1 on type error */
7772 
7773  vim_memset(str, NUL, sizeof(str));
7774 
7775  if (rettv_list_alloc(rettv) != FAIL)
7776  {
7777  if (lnum >= 1 && lnum <= curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count
7778  && col >= 0 && col <= (long)STRLEN(ml_get(lnum))
7779  && curwin->w_p_cole > 0)
7780  {
7781  (void)syn_get_id(curwin, lnum, col, FALSE, NULL, FALSE);
7782  syntax_flags = get_syntax_info(&matchid);
7783 
7784  /* get the conceal character */
7785  if ((syntax_flags & HL_CONCEAL) && curwin->w_p_cole < 3)
7786  {
7787  cchar = syn_get_sub_char();
7788  if (cchar == NUL && curwin->w_p_cole == 1)
7789  cchar = (lcs_conceal == NUL) ? ' ' : lcs_conceal;
7790  if (cchar != NUL)
7791  {
7792  if (has_mbyte)
7793  (*mb_char2bytes)(cchar, str);
7794  else
7795  str[0] = cchar;
7796  }
7797  }
7798  }
7799 
7800  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list,
7801  (syntax_flags & HL_CONCEAL) != 0);
7802  /* -1 to auto-determine strlen */
7803  list_append_string(rettv->vval.v_list, str, -1);
7804  list_append_number(rettv->vval.v_list, matchid);
7805  }
7806 #endif
7807 }

7968 /*
7969  * "tr(string, fromstr, tostr)" function
7970  */
7971  static void
7972 f_tr(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
7973 {
7974  char_u *in_str;
7975  char_u *fromstr;
7976  char_u *tostr;
7977  char_u *p;
7978  int inlen;
7979  int fromlen;
7980  int tolen;
7981  int idx;
7982  char_u *cpstr;
7983  int cplen;
7984  int first = TRUE;
7985  char_u buf[NUMBUFLEN];
7986  char_u buf2[NUMBUFLEN];
7987  garray_T ga;
7988 
7989  in_str = tv_get_string(&argvars[0]);
7990  fromstr = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[1], buf);
7991  tostr = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[2], buf2);
7992 
7993  /* Default return value: empty string. */
7994  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
7995  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
7996  if (fromstr == NULL || tostr == NULL)
7997  return; /* type error; errmsg already given */
7998  ga_init2(&ga, (int)sizeof(char), 80);
7999 
8000  if (!has_mbyte)
8001  /* not multi-byte: fromstr and tostr must be the same length */
8002  if (STRLEN(fromstr) != STRLEN(tostr))
8003  {
8004 error:
8005  semsg(_(e_invarg2), fromstr);
8006  ga_clear(&ga);
8007  return;
8008  }
8009 
8010  /* fromstr and tostr have to contain the same number of chars */
8011  while (*in_str != NUL)
8012  {
8013  if (has_mbyte)
8014  {
8015  inlen = (*mb_ptr2len)(in_str);
8016  cpstr = in_str;
8017  cplen = inlen;
8018  idx = 0;
8019  for (p = fromstr; *p != NUL; p += fromlen)
8020  {
8021  fromlen = (*mb_ptr2len)(p);
8022  if (fromlen == inlen && STRNCMP(in_str, p, inlen) == 0)
8023  {
8024  for (p = tostr; *p != NUL; p += tolen)
8025  {
8026  tolen = (*mb_ptr2len)(p);
8027  if (idx-- == 0)
8028  {
8029  cplen = tolen;
8030  cpstr = p;
8031  break;
8032  }
8033  }
8034  if (*p == NUL) /* tostr is shorter than fromstr */
8035  goto error;
8036  break;
8037  }
8038  ++idx;
8039  }
8040 
8041  if (first && cpstr == in_str)
8042  {
8043  /* Check that fromstr and tostr have the same number of
8044  * (multi-byte) characters. Done only once when a character
8045  * of in_str doesn't appear in fromstr. */
8046  first = FALSE;
8047  for (p = tostr; *p != NUL; p += tolen)
8048  {
8049  tolen = (*mb_ptr2len)(p);
8050  --idx;
8051  }
8052  if (idx != 0)
8053  goto error;
8054  }
8055 
8056  (void)ga_grow(&ga, cplen);
8057  mch_memmove((char *)ga.ga_data + ga.ga_len, cpstr, (size_t)cplen);
8058  ga.ga_len += cplen;
8059 
8060  in_str += inlen;
8061  }
8062  else
8063  {
8064  /* When not using multi-byte chars we can do it faster. */
8065  p = vim_strchr(fromstr, *in_str);
8066  if (p != NULL)
8067  ga_append(&ga, tostr[p - fromstr]);
8068  else
8069  ga_append(&ga, *in_str);
8070  ++in_str;
8071  }
8072  }
8073 
8074  /* add a terminating NUL */
8075  (void)ga_grow(&ga, 1);
8076  ga_append(&ga, NUL);
8077 
8078  rettv->vval.v_string = ga.ga_data;
8079 }
8080 
8081 /*
8082  * "trim({expr})" function
8083  */
8084  static void
8085 f_trim(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
8086 {
8087  char_u buf1[NUMBUFLEN];
8088  char_u buf2[NUMBUFLEN];
8089  char_u *head = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[0], buf1);
8090  char_u *mask = NULL;
8091  char_u *tail;
8092  char_u *prev;
8093  char_u *p;
8094  int c1;
8095 
8096  rettv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
8097  if (head == NULL)
8098  {
8099  rettv->vval.v_string = NULL;
8100  return;
8101  }
8102 
8103  if (argvars[1].v_type == VAR_STRING)
8104  mask = tv_get_string_buf_chk(&argvars[1], buf2);
8105 
8106  while (*head != NUL)
8107  {
8108  c1 = PTR2CHAR(head);
8109  if (mask == NULL)
8110  {
8111  if (c1 > ' ' && c1 != 0xa0)
8112  break;
8113  }
8114  else
8115  {
8116  for (p = mask; *p != NUL; MB_PTR_ADV(p))
8117  if (c1 == PTR2CHAR(p))
8118  break;
8119  if (*p == NUL)
8120  break;
8121  }
8122  MB_PTR_ADV(head);
8123  }
8124 
8125  for (tail = head + STRLEN(head); tail > head; tail = prev)
8126  {
8127  prev = tail;
8128  MB_PTR_BACK(head, prev);
8129  c1 = PTR2CHAR(prev);
8130  if (mask == NULL)
8131  {
8132  if (c1 > ' ' && c1 != 0xa0)
8133  break;
8134  }
8135  else
8136  {
8137  for (p = mask; *p != NUL; MB_PTR_ADV(p))
8138  if (c1 == PTR2CHAR(p))
8139  break;
8140  if (*p == NUL)
8141  break;
8142  }
8143  }
8144  rettv->vval.v_string = vim_strnsave(head, (int)(tail - head));
8145 }
8146 
8147 #ifdef FEAT_FLOAT
8148 /*
8149  * "trunc({float})" function
8150  */
8151  static void
8152 f_trunc(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
8153 {
8154  float_T f = 0.0;
8155 
8156  rettv->v_type = VAR_FLOAT;
8157  if (get_float_arg(argvars, &f) == OK)
8158  /* trunc() is not in C90, use floor() or ceil() instead. */
8159  rettv->vval.v_float = f > 0 ? floor(f) : ceil(f);
8160  else
8161  rettv->vval.v_float = 0.0;
8162 }
8163 #endif
8164 
8165 /*
8166  * "type(expr)" function
8167  */
8168  static void
8169 f_type(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
8170 {
8171  int n = -1;
8172 
8173  switch (argvars[0].v_type)
8174  {
8175  case VAR_NUMBER: n = VAR_TYPE_NUMBER; break;
8176  case VAR_STRING: n = VAR_TYPE_STRING; break;
8177  case VAR_PARTIAL:
8178  case VAR_FUNC: n = VAR_TYPE_FUNC; break;
8179  case VAR_LIST: n = VAR_TYPE_LIST; break;
8180  case VAR_DICT: n = VAR_TYPE_DICT; break;
8181  case VAR_FLOAT: n = VAR_TYPE_FLOAT; break;
8182  case VAR_SPECIAL:
8183  if (argvars[0].vval.v_number == VVAL_FALSE
8184  || argvars[0].vval.v_number == VVAL_TRUE)
8185  n = VAR_TYPE_BOOL;
8186  else
8187  n = VAR_TYPE_NONE;
8188  break;
8189  case VAR_JOB: n = VAR_TYPE_JOB; break;
8190  case VAR_CHANNEL: n = VAR_TYPE_CHANNEL; break;
8191  case VAR_BLOB: n = VAR_TYPE_BLOB; break;
8192  case VAR_UNKNOWN:
8193  internal_error("f_type(UNKNOWN)");
8194  n = -1;
8195  break;
8196  }
8197  rettv->vval.v_number = n;
8198 }
8199 
8200 /*
8201  * "virtcol(string)" function
8202  */
8203  static void
8204 f_virtcol(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv)
8205 {
8206  colnr_T vcol = 0;
8207  pos_T *fp;
8208  int fnum = curbuf->b_fnum;
8209 
8210  fp = var2fpos(&argvars[0], FALSE, &fnum);
8211  if (fp != NULL && fp->lnum <= curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count
8212  && fnum == curbuf->b_fnum)
8213  {
8214  getvvcol(curwin, fp, NULL, NULL, &vcol);
8215  ++vcol;
8216  }
8217 
8218  rettv->vval.v_number = vcol;
8219 }

8235  if (non_zero_arg(&argvars[0]))
8236  curbuf->b_visual_mode_eval = NUL;
8237 }
